title: six vegetable salad
directions: Put salt and enough water to cover first 4 items and let set for 4 hours.
Drain well.
Add the rest of the vegetables.

title: special oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients to a soft ball.
Make out in small balls and roll in sugar.
Flatten and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet that has been sprayed with a nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg very carefully until crumbly. Put 3/4 cups aside for top.
Press remaining into 9 x 13 pan.
Mix pumpkin, pumpkin pie spice 2 eggs and milk.
Stir and pour on top. Add 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon to reserve and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for almost 1 hour.
Knife in side will come out clean.

title: strawberry pretzel delight
directions: Combine pretzels, melted margarine and sugar; press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes, then cool.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and brown sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, gumdrops and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 350°.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: cherry pie
directions: Combine sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice.
Add drained pineapple and pie filling.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts. Turn into baked pie crusts.
Garnish as desired with additional Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: fisher's ham bits
directions: Slice ham thin, then into strips.
Brown lightly to complete cooking.
Drain.
Add pepper jelly; simmer.
Serve hot.

title: grandma friedrich's bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla and nutmeg.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour or more.
Pats of butter on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook shells and cheese as directed on box.
Saute onion.
Add rest of ingredients.
Heat.
Add shells and cheese.
Mix well. Put in a casserole dish.
May sprinkle grated cheese on top, as desired.
Bake at 325° to 350° until bubbly.

title: skillet hamburger pie
directions: In skillet, cook beef, celery and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in drained beans, mushroom soup, Worcestershire sauce, 1/4 cup water, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Simmer to blend flavors, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: graham cracker layered cookies
directions: Line a greased 9 x 13 pan with whole graham crackers. Stir to blend the melted butter, sugar, egg and milk; bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add nuts, coconut, graham cracker crumbs and vanilla. Pour over layer of crackers and cover with another layer of graham crackers. Cover with icing.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: *I use frozen pepper halves in the winter and fill them while they are frozen.

title: all occasion punch
directions: Put all ingredients in a gallon plastic jug and finish filling with water.
Shake before pouring.
May be frozen and served a "slush".

title: mazola sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add Mazola oil.
Beat sugar, vanilla and egg mixture with mixer until light and fluffy. Add flour mixture and mix well.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Roll out on floured board; cut into desired shapes.
Cook at 400° for 9 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: microwave lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef; add spaghetti sauce.
In a separate bowl mix water, egg and cottage cheese.
In oblong glass dish put a single layer of uncooked noodles.
Top with a layer of beef mixture, then a layer of cheese mixture.
Repeat with noodles, beef and cheese. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Heat 8 minutes on High.
Cover and heat 30 to 32 minutes on power level 5. Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: double cheese burgers
directions: Combine beef, salsa, salt and pepper; mix lightly together. Form into 4 oval patties 1/2-inch thick.
Place on broiler pan rack.
Broil 10 to 12 minutes; turn once.
Combine tomato and salsa; top half of each tortilla with equal portions of lettuce, salsa, burger and the cheeses.
Fold tortilla over burger.
Serves 4.

title: pear bread
directions: Cream butter; beat in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla and pears.

title: chicken casserole(or turkey)
directions: Mix all together, except enough cheese to spread over top. Place in casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
May be prepared the day before and placed in refrigerator overnight. Flavors will blend in.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix in order given.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine spinach, eggs, crumbled bacon, cheese and onions in large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and dressing; mix well.
Serve over spinach.

title: pigs without blankets
directions: Brown onion, celery, pepper and hamburg in butter.
Mix soup, tomato juice and seasonings.
Layer in greased 4-quart casserole: 1/2 cabbage, 1/2 potatoes, all of meat mixture and 1/2 sauce. Repeat layers.
Top with bacon strips.
Do not cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix crumbs with melted margarine.
Press into bottom of 8 inch pie plate.

title: easy garden bake(low fat)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Layer zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese in pie plate.
Stir remaining ingredients until blended.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake for 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Let jello stand until it starts to jell.
Then add other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: chicken with poppy seed
directions: Place cut up chicken in greased casserole dish (9 x 13). Mix in separate bowl: sour cream and soup until well blended. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with poppy seeds. Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top of mixture. Melt butter and pour over crackers. Sprinkle more poppy seeds on top. Bake at 350° until hot, about 30-45 minutes.

title: my family's christmas eggs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown and drain sausage and set aside.
Add eggs, mustard, milk and salt.
Beat one minute on medium.
Stir in cheese, bread and sausage.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan, ungreased. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be doubled, tripled or quadrupled.

title: green tomato ketchup
directions: Cook 2 1/2 hours in oven at 350° with cover on.
Bottle while hot.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix sugar, ground celery seed and milk into mayonnaise. Add vinegar and whisk until smooth. Add cole slaw mix. Stir until mixed well. Refrigerate to chill and serve.

title: zucchini nibbles
directions: Lightly mix all ingredients.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: low-fat apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients right down the line.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: northern bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight or boil for 2 minutes and rinse well.
Add to beans, tomato sauce, pork hocks, onion, salt, pepper and garlic. Cover and simmer about 2 hours until done.
Remove pork hocks and trim off fat; cut pork in small pieces.
Add pork, celery, carrots and mashed potatoes to beans.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are done (45 minutes).

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need a flowerpot, wooden or silk flowers and gummy worms.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Wash and sort peas; drain.
Soak overnight.
Next day add seasoning; bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 1 hour or until tender.
Don't stir to avoid excess breaking of peas.
Serves 6.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and bake in a covered casserole for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: quick pie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch bake dish with margarine.
Pour cherries in bake dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over cherries.
Sprinkle nuts over top of cake mix.
Melt margarine; pour over nuts.
Sprinkle sugar on top for a glaze. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: cheese icebox rounds
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Starting with the first and ending with the last, mix thoroughly.
Roll in rounds with waxed paper.
Let chill for several hours or overnight.
Slice and bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.
Best not baked too brown.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Will last for several weeks in refrigerator.

title: creamed broccoli soup
directions: Cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour.
Add broth and 1 package frozen broccoli.
Simmer 1 hour. Put vegetables through a food mill or puree in blender.
Return to broth.
Add second package of broccoli and cheese.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes until broccoli is tender and cheese is melted.
Add cream if desired.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Boil 9 cups water; add white rice and noodle soup and boil 3 minutes.
Brown sausage and drain.
In drippings, saute onion and bell pepper.
Add all to soup mix.
Then add mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake uncovered 1 hour at 350°.
This can be made ahead and frozen.

title: deviled meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly. Shape into 16 small balls. Saute slowly in skillet until browned and done. Serve as is or on picks. Alternate meatballs with olives, pickled onions, cheese cubes, etc. Makes 16 appetizers.

title: pig cake
directions: Mix well.
Add oranges and beat until well mixed.
Bake in long pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Place 4 or 5 whole green beans in third piece of bacon.
Fold over one time.
Place on 13x9-inch casserole dish.
Continue until green beans are used.
Sprinkle each bundle with brown sugar.
Bake at 325 degrees for 15 minutes.
Turn oven up to 400 degrees and cook until bacon is done.
If cooking two cans of beans, two 13x9-inch dishes will be needed.

title: microwave cranberry jelly
directions: Combine juice and Sure-Jell in a 3-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on High for 11 to 13 minutes or until mixture boils. Stir once during cooking.
Stir in sugar.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until mixture boils hard for 1 minute.
Skim off foam.
Pour into jars.
Makes 6 cups.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Cook in oven for 1 hour at 350°.
If you double this recipe, cook 1 1/2 hours or longer until rice is soft and dry.

title: surprise fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs until light; add sugar.
Mix well.
Add margarine, flour, cocoa, vanilla and salt.
Stir well.
Grease and flour glass pie plate.
Sprinkle with layer of chopped nuts.
Pour in pie mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with Cool Whip or the like.

title: no-fat grilled potato slices
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spread potatoes on prepared pan; sprinkle herb mixture on potatoes.
Bake about 10 minutes and then turn and bake again for 10 minutes.
The thinner the slices, the quicker they bake.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Wash, peel and shred potatoes.
Drain completely.
Beat eggs in small mixing bowl until thick and lemon colored.
Mix in potatoes, onion, flour and salt.
Heat oil in skillet over low heat or in electric frypan.
Shape potato mixture into patties. Place in skillet.
Cook over medium or low heat, turning once, until golden brown, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Can be served with applesauce, sour cream or ketchup.

title: lemon grilled salmon
directions: In a small bowl, mix together dill, lemon-pepper, salt and garlic powder.
Sprinkle on salmon.
Place in a large resealable plastic bag or shallow glass container.
Combine brown sugar, broth, oil, soy sauce and green onions.
Pour over the salmon. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Turn once.

title: vanilla sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar with an electric mixer.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour one cup at a time, mixing them together.
The dough will be very stiff; blend flour in by hand.
Don't chill dough.
Divide into two balls.
On floured surface, roll each ball into a 12-inch circle in diameter and 1/8-inch thick.
Then cut out your cookies.
Bake cookies on an ungreased sheet on top rack for 6 to 7 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In saucepan, melt Crisco; remove from heat.
Stir in cocoa and salt.
Mix in milk and vanilla.
In mixer bowl, stir cocoa mixture into sugar; beat at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth and creamy.
Add 1 tablespoon more milk, if needed, for good spreading consistency.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well. Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet and remove to wire rack.

title: 6 weeks bran muffins
directions: Mix bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 60 muffins. Store in refrigerator.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add whole egg and vanilla; beat well.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt and cream of tartar; gradually add to mixture.
Chill dough for 1 hour.

title: copper dollars
directions: Peel and slice carrots into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place in saucepan; add boiling water to cover and cook 15 minutes, until crisp-tender.
Drain and cool.
Slice and separate onion into rings; seed green pepper and cut into strips.
Combine carrots, onion and pepper in large bowl.
In saucepan, combine sugar, soup, vinegar, oil, Worcestershire and mustard.
Heat to boiling, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and pour over vegetables; mix well.
Divide mixture between 2 quart jars, cover and refrigerate.
Serve cold as a salad relish side dish, alone or over fresh greens.
Makes 8 cups.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook until thickened.
Cool and add 1 cup whipping cream (whipped).
Mix well and chill.

title: jeanette's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt and add to first mixture.
Add chips and nutmeats.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: rum pie "caribe"
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Soak gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Place over low heat; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Pour this over egg yolks in slow stream, beating constantly.
Cool mixture.
Stir in dark Jamaican rum. Whip cream until stiff, then fold into the egg mixture.
Cool filling, but before it begins to set, pour into pie shells.

title: triple layer bars
directions: In oven at 350°, melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
(For glass pan, bake at 325°.)
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine (make sure all crumbs are moistened; drizzle on more melted margarine if necessary).
Top evenly with coconut and pecans; pour on sweetened condensed milk.
Bake for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: popcorn
directions: Mix popcorn, potatoes and nuts. Sprinkle dill weed, lemon pepper, garlic powder, onion powder and salt over mixture and toss to mix. Add Worcestershire sauce to melted margarine and pour over the seasoned mixture, tossing to coat evenly. Spread in a shallow pan and bake for about 10 minutes at 350°, stirring once or twice during baking. Yield: 2 1/2 quarts.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix cream cheese, peanut butter and sugar together.
Prepare Dream Whip by the package; mix all together until smooth.
Place in pie crust; place in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: cracker spread
directions: Cut beef into small pieces.
Mix with other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: poached pears(lo-cal)
directions: Peel pears, leaving stems on.
In saucepan, heat juices, vanilla and cinnamon to a simmer.
Add pears; simmer for 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered, turning pears occasionally until tender. Remove pears.
Reduce syrup 30 to 35 minutes to 1 1/2 cups. Strain.
Stir in raisins and cool syrup to room temperature. Serve pears in small glass bowls.
Spoon raisins and syrup over and around pears.

title: easy seven layer dip
directions: In serving dish, layer in order given.
Chill and serve with Fritos corn chips.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix egg, sugar, salt and vanilla thoroughly.
Slowly stir in the hot milk.
Pour at once into unbaked pastry shell.
Top with nutmeg.
Bake in hot oven at 475° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 425° and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until a knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
After you have mixed your hot milk with the rest of the ingredients, add your favorite fresh fruit or berries (3/4 to 1 cup) and bake.

title: berry pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Gradually add water; stir until smooth.
Cook on medium heat until mixture comes to a boil (stirring constantly).
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.

title: zesty mushroom soup by m and r
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Cook and stir 5 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Add flour, tarragon, pepper and salt.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes, until thickens slightly.
Serves 2.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together flour and cinnamon, then beat together eggs, sugar and oil.
Add dry mixture to liquid mixture and stir in 2 cups pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix first 5 ingredients together; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to first group. By spoonfuls, roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: cherry jubilee cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Do not stretch pie pastry too thin. Make high fluted edge.
Pour cherry filling into shell.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: creole pork chops
directions: In a skillet, brown chops in shortening.
On each chop place a lemon slice and an onion slice.
Mix together the brown sugar, catsup and water.
Pour over chops.
Cook covered until tender, about 1 hour.

title: hope's baked beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp; crumble and save bacon grease. Fry hamburger with onions until brown. Drain. Combine all ingredients in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: little goodies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Form into small balls and bake at 350° until brown.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: vegetarian cottage cheese loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in oiled flat casserole and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with brown gravy or cranberry sauce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: imitation peanut brittle
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and syrup until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Pour over the cornflakes. Cool and break into pieces.

title: gourmet stew
directions: *May substitute round steak, cut in 1-inch strips.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except potato chips. Spoon into a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Cover with potato chips and bake at 450° for 15-20 minutes, or until heated through.

title: fried turkey
directions: Mix all seasonings together.
Cover turkey or breast of turkey completely with mixed seasonings.
Put in a Ziploc bag and refrigerate at least 2 days.
Heat peanut oil to 300° in deep fat fryer and maintain 300° throughout cooking.
Fry turkey in deep fat fryer 5 minutes per pound.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, egg, soda, salt, vanilla and milk and blend in flour.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of moistened glass which has been dipped in sugar.
Sprinkle more sugar on top.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until well blended.
Add milk all at once.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans and soup.
Layer beans and cheese in baking dish.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Last 5 minutes, put onion rings on top to brown.
Also use cheese or almonds on top if desired.

title: broccoli-rice quiche
directions: Cook rice.
Add onions to broccoli and cook.
Combine rice, 1/2 cup cheese, 1 egg and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Press firmly in a greased 9-inch pan to form crust.
Combine broccoli, milk, pepper, mushrooms, eggs and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Mix.
Spoon into crust. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: crepes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add wet ingredients. Lightly butter a
6-8 inch skillet.
Pour 1/4 c. of mixture into skillet - rotate skillet until crepe is done.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Serve.
You can use pie filling also.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on a rack.

title: lillie's butterscotch brownies
directions: Put butter and oleo on low heat to melt and then add remaining ingredients. Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool brownies and spread with icing.

title: lemon pie
directions: *Use only 2 cups of water when making filling.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups hot water and one cup of cold water. Then add 1 cup of cranberry juice from can.
Add cranberries. Stir well.
Let set in refrigerator until just about solid.
Then line top with whole pieces of pecans.
Let finish congealing and serve.

title: my kinda cookie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter, sugars, oil, egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Stir in coconut, cereal, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add 2 tablespoons olive oil. Stir in onions and salt.
Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally for 20 to 30 minutes until onions are golden brown.
Sprinkle flour over onions and cook, stirring for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
In another pan, heat stock to simmering, then pour into the onions.
Simmer partially covered for 30 to 40 minutes.
While the soup simmers, make croutons.
Place bread on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put milk into a large pot with high flame and bring to a boil. Add rice and salt.
With medium-low flame, cook about 30 minutes with cover off; stir often.

title: shrimp on english muffins
directions: Mix and spread on English muffins.
Put grated cheese on and place in oven until cheese is melted.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix
together cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg; spread in floured pan.
Mix together powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese; spread over top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast cake in lukewarm water.
Add 1 cup mashed potatoes, melted shortening, sugar and salt.
Cover and let stand in a warm place about 2 hours or until it bubbles.
Add flour; beat well.
Cover and chill about 1 1/2 hours before serving time. Shape in rolls.
Brush with butter and let stand until double in size.

title: taffy apples
directions: Wash and dry 10 eating apples; insert a wooden skewer in blossom end of apple.
Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in top of double boiler; cook over direct heat, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Add oil of cloves and little red food coloring. Continue cooking without stirring until a drop of mixture tested in cold water forms a hard piece that cracks easily (290° on candy thermometer).
Set pan over boiling water.
Dip each apple into syrup quickly.
Remove and whirl apple until syrup covers.

title: stuffed fish
directions: Utensils needed:
One large cutting board, spoon, bowl, 1 baking pan, 2 feet of thin foil, 2 to 3 large ti leaves and 1 Habachi or oven.

title: layered tortilla dip
directions: Layer:
Mix beans with taco seasoning.
Mix sour cream with taco seasoning.
Sprinkle sliced olives to cover.
Cover olives with tomatoes.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice each tomato into 3 thick slices.
Pour evaporated milk in small bowl and place 1 cup flour and the bread crumbs in separate piles on waxed paper.
Dip tomatoes in flour, then milk, then crumbs, coating well.
Place in refrigerator to dry for about one hour.
Fry bacon in large skillet until crisp; remove and set aside.
In bacon drippings, saute tomato slices until brown.
Pour off all but two tablespoons of drippings.
Add remaining flour; cook and stir for two minutes more.
Season to taste.
To serve, place tomato slice on plate; pour sauce over and top with a bacon slice.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Add eggs and beat.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with remaining milk. Add vanilla and hot water.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: monterey chicken
directions: Heat oil in cast-iron skillet.
Add chicken.
Cook until white all the way through and outside is dark brown.
(Skillet must be hot, but don't burn the oil.)
Add garlic and onion; cook until onion is soft.
Add mushrooms and tomatoes; cook until it's heated all through.
Remove chicken.

title: beans for a bunch
directions: Brown beef and place in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onion and place in crock-pot.
Add other ingredients.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: spaghetti and cheese
directions: Boil spaghetti in salted water until done.
Drain.
Add butter, milk and cheese over low heat; stir in until butter and cheese are melted.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
(If mushrooms are very large, use melon baller to make cavity deeper.)
Mix cream cheese and onion soup mix with lemon juice.
Fill cavities of mushrooms.
Put under broiler until lightly browned.
Enjoy!

title: filled drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well. Dissolve baking soda in warm water; add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, flour and salt.
Drop dough by spoon on greased cookie sheet; make hollow in center.
Put in 1 teaspoon of filling and place 1 teaspoon of dough on top to cover filling.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: melba milk
directions: Combine strawberries and peaches with their syrups in blender until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and beat about 1 to 2 seconds.

title: summer salad bowl
directions: Wash and hull fresh strawberries.
Wash and drain fresh blueberries.
Place thawed peaches in large container.
Mix in prepared strawberries and blueberries.
Stir in strawberry glaze. Keep refrigerated.

title: vanilla cream pie(low-fat)
directions: Stir sweetener, cornstarch and salt in saucepan. Blend milk and egg yolks. Gradually stir into sugar mixture. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens and boils. Boil and stir 1 minute. Remove from heat; blend in butter and vanilla. Immediately pour into baked pie shell.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Combine blueberries, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water in pan. Cook on low heat (15 minutes).
Combine cornstarch and 3 tablespoons water in bowl; mix well.
Add cornstarch mix to blueberries; cook until thick.
Cool.
Combine flour, butter and pecans in bowl.
Mix well.
Press dough into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread topping over cooled crust.
Pour blueberry mixture over top of cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Cream cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
When well blended, add 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Set aside.
Mix together crushed pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted margarine.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread cream cheese mixture over pretzel mix.
Mix 2 small boxes strawberry jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries (still frozen).
Stir together and refrigerate until it starts to set. (It won't take long.)
Pour over cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate several hours until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: coffee
directions: Make coffee.
Into pot, put all other ingredients.
Let steep 1 minute.
Serve.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: onions on the side
directions: Lay 1/2 of the onions in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2 pan. In a small bowl, pour the soup and water. Crush the potato chips. Top 1/2 on soup; repeat. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or so. Eat with grilled ribs or steak.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Combine cake mix, egg whites, water and 2 tablespoons creme de menthe.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed with electric mixer. Reduce speed to low; beat 1 minute.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Let cake cool completely in pan.
Spread fudge topping over cake.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt.
Beat egg yolk; add milk to make 2/3 cup.
Mix like pie crust.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out 1/2 the dough, place in greased cookie sheet.
Layer with cornflakes.
Cut apples, mix with cinnamon and sugar.
Put this mixture on top of cornflakes.
Dot with butter.
Place second half of dough which is also rolled out, on top of apples.
Beat egg white, spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until nice and brown.
Glaze while hot with a mixture of powdered sugar and water. Make into thin paste.
If apples are juicy, add 2 tablespoons of flour to mixture.

title: instant chocolate milk
directions: Mix together and keep in tight covered container.
For 1 cup of hot chocolate, use 1/3 cup of mix to 1 cup water.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Brown meat and add taco seasoning mix according to package directions.
In a greased casserole dish layer Doritos chips, first 4 ingredients mixture, cheese and meat mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potted dirt
directions: Combine cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar in bowl; mix well.
Combine milk and pudding mix in mixer bowl.
Beat well. Fold in whipped topping.
Alternate layers of cookie crumbs, cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture in 8-inch flowerpot, ending with cookie crumbs.
Chill until set.
Garnish with silk flowers just before serving.
Yields 15 servings.

title: sunday yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Cover and let stand 8 hours or overnight on kitchen counter.
Turn onto floured board and knead lightly.
Roll out to 1 to 2-inch thickness.
Cut into rolls on greased cookie sheet and let rise 4 to 6 hours.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Use muffin tins to make cloverleaf rolls.

title: dutch funnel cakes
directions: Mix together ingredients in a pan thoroughly.
Place enough lard in a pan to cover the bottom.
Let it get quite hot before cooking the batter.
Put the batter through a funnel into the hot lard, beginning at center of pan and turning the stream around in a gradually enlarging circle, being careful not to touch the sides or the other dough.
Fry a light brown and serve hot with any tart jelly.

title: scrambled eggs and corn
directions: Fry bacon crisp and put on paper towel.
Now chop up the garlic, onion and pepper fine and cook in bacon fat until tender. Add drained corn and cook for 2 minutes.
Beat up eggs, milk, salt, pepper and Tabasco until well mixed.
Pour over vegetables. Stir with fork until almost done.
Chip bacon and fold into egg mixture.
Serves 4.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Melt butter; then cool.
Add brown sugar, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Then beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, oatmeal, corn flakes, pecans and chocolate chips.
Dip into cookie sheet with ice cream dipper and bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: three-c casserole
directions: Crush corn chips in package.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Layer the corn chips, chili, onion and cheese; repeat layers.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken pieces.
Butter bottom of pan.
Put ingredients together and put cornflake crumbs or potato chips (crushed) or crackers (crushed) on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: festive corn salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into a bowl lined with lettuce leaves.
Serve with a slotted spoon.
Mayonnaise or salad dressing may be substituted for Italian salad dressing.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Substitute cherry juice for liquid called for
on package directions.
Add halved cherries to batter.
Bake as directed.

title: oatmeal date cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly butter cookie sheets.
Cream butter and brown sugar.
Beat in honey and eggs until smooth.
Sift flour, cinnamon and salt together.
Stir into butter mixture.
Add oats, pecans, raisins and dates.
Stir well until mixed.
Shape dough into 2 inch balls.
Place 9 balls on each cookie sheet and flatten each one to make large cookies.
Bake about 15 minutes, until slightly browned.
Cool on wire rack.

title: scotchies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and add sugar gradually.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture, oats, nuts and coconut.
Roll in balls or drop from spoon.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes and remove from pan immediately.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Slice potatoes and onions 1/4-inch thick. Place in oblong casserole dish sprayed with Pam. Salt and pepper potatoes. Add cream of mushroom soup and melted margarine. Add Cheez Whiz. Put pork chops on top. You may layer this in a deeper casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: summer tortellini salad
directions: Cook pasta, drain and rinse under cold water.
Toss all ingredients together chill and serve.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Rinse chipped beef in cold water and chop coarsely.
Saute onion in butter.
Add beef and saute 5 minutes.
Add cream cheese and milk.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts and combines with milk.
Add grated cheese, mushrooms, pepper and Beau Monde.
Mix all until hot.
Serve with torn pumpernickel bread to dip.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Cook sugar and pineapple with juice on
stove 5 minutes.
Add gelatine diluted with 2 tablespoons water.
Mix in cream cheese. Let cool to room temperature.
Add whipped cream and chill until set.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in uncooked pie shell for 10 minutes at 450°, then reduce oven to 350° and bake 35 minutes more.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix gelatin and pineapple in a large saucepan.
Heat on stove until gelatin dissolves and just comes to a boil.
Allow to cool. Mix in buttermilk and Cool Whip until blended.
Pour in an 8 x 12-inch dish. Chill.

title: cheese dip
directions: Fry sausage; drain.
Add to tomatoes and cheese, put all in a slow cooker and cook until cheese is melted.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes.
Cool before adding other ingredients.
Put in quart
containers and freeze.
Mix 1 quart ginger ale to 1 quart frozen punch.
Serves 30.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Start adding sugar slowly.
When stiff, add chips, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Put in oven and turn off oven heat.
Leave overnight or several hours.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together, then stir in milk and butter and place on stove in an iron pan.
Bring to boil and boil 2 minutes for fudge or 1 minute for icing.
Place in pan of cold water and beat until cool.
Add flavoring and pecans.

title: whole-grain cherry crisp
directions: Pour pie filling into 9-inch round baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in food processor; mix until crumbly.
Pat evenly over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve warm or cold with ice cream or whipped topping.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Thoroughly mix jello powder with Cool Whip.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Add optional ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Form above into oval patties, brown, put in casserole dish.

title: marguerite's new york cheese cake(makes 10 servings; make the day before serving.)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a mixer bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, butter, sour cream, cornstarch, vanilla and lemon juice; mix. Then add eggs (one at a time). Place batter in greased spring-form pan. Place in larger pan containing approximately 1-inch water. Bake one hour. Enjoy.

title: green chile bake
directions: Spread out rolls; do not separate.
Mix cream cheese, chiles and onions together.
Spread onto the spread-out dough.
Roll like you were rolling a jelly roll.
Wrap in wax paper or plastic wrap. Freeze.
Cut into pieces and bake at 325° until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: In medium saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until mixture begins to bubble. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese.
Mix well and set aside.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Soften oleo and cream with sugar.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: corn relish
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, salt, vinegar, Tabasco sauce, turmeric, mustard and celery seed.
Bring to a boil and cook several minutes.
Add vegetables and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Seal in hot jars.

title: kahlua stir-fry chicken
directions: Coat chicken in mixture of egg, 2 tablespoons oil and cornstarch.
Heat remaining oil in wok or skillet.
Add chicken. Cook until golden brown.
Drain well.
Remove all but 2 tablespoons oil from wok; heat.
Add all vegetables except green onions.
Stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes.
Add Kahlua-cornstarch mixture. Bring to boil, then simmer to slightly thicken.
Add chicken and cashews.
Heat.
Remove to serving platter.
Garnish with green onions.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: eggs in casserole
directions: Crumble buttered bread in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Crumble bacon over bread.
Grate both types of cheese over the bacon. Beat the eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over cheeses.
Cover baking dish with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable pull apart bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Saute in oleo, onion and green pepper.
Cook 1/2 pound bacon crisp and crumble it.
Mix bacon with vegetables and biscuits.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Pour into ungreased Bundt pan.
Cook in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
(Ham can be substituted for bacon.)

title: brownies
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa together.
Beat egg and vanilla and add to dry mixture.
Melt butter and pour over mixture and stir. Add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Into a large mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, spices and brown sugar only.
Whisk until smooth and spices are evenly distributed. Add Eagle Brand milk and eggs; mix well.
Pour into pie shell and put into oven immediately.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes then reduce heat to 350° and bake about 45 minutes longer.
Pie will test done with a clean knife as for custards.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: corn casserole
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder and beans.
Put Doritos in casserole dish.
Pour hamburger mixture on top of chips.
Mix slightly.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix together ingredients and spoon batter onto grease baking sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add other ingredients.
Mix juice of 3 lemons, strained and 1 cup sugar, stirring occasionally over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 3 pans. Bake at 350° for one hour.
When bread is done, take out of pan and place on foil or wax paper to wrap.
Spoon lemon mixture over loaves till all is gone.
Cool and wrap. Freeze.
This makes it easier to slice.
It is better if frozen for 2 to 3 days.
May be frozen longer.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: doc's famous irish bread
directions: Work shortening into flour.
Add other dry ingredients.
Add milk and mix well.
Place in a large, greased iron skillet.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 300°.
Continue to bake for 45 minutes.
Dot with butter when removed from the oven.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Mix with cheese, cubed, into meat.
Spread on party rye or pumpernickel bread.
Freeze.
When frozen, put in plastic bag and use as needed.
Just before serving, bake at 350° for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix coating mixture and ginger in shaker bag.
Coat chicken as directed on package.
Bake 15 minutes on ungreased or foil lined 15 x 10-inch metal baking pan.
Mix preserves and soy sauce in small bowl until well blended.
Drizzle over chicken. Bake 5 minutes or until chicken is cooked through. Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time:
5 minutes.
Cooking time: 20 minutes.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese and mix together all ingredients.
Form into ball and roll in pecan crumbs.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add prepared spaghetti sauce, mushrooms and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle nuts in bottom of a greased Bundt or angel food pan. Mix cinnamon and 1 cup brown sugar in small bowl.
Cut each biscuit in fourths with scissors.
Roll biscuits in cinnamon-sugar mixture and layer biscuits in pan.
Blend remaining 1 cup brown sugar with melted margarine and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 to 25 minutes more.
Cook in pan 10 minutes, then invert on rack.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Combine wafers, butter, pecans and press firmly 1/2 of this mixture into bottom of 9x13 baking dish.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, milk; beat until creamy and spread on top of crust. Put remaining half of wafer mixture on top.
Beat whipped cream until stiff; spread over second wafter mixture.
Spread cherry pie filling over top.
Refrigerate; will keep several days.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix cake mix and yeast in bowl.
Add salt and gradually stir in warm water, then flour and mix.
Cover for one hour.
Divide dough into 3 equal parts.
Roll out to a 24 x 10-inch rectangle. Spread surface with softened butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Place on greased jelly roll pan or others, cut side down. Cover and let rise 2 to 3 hours.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked lemon pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Add salt to egg whites; beat, gradually adding 1/2 cup sugar, until stiff (meringue).

title: double butterscotch cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Cream together butter and dry pudding mix until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and corn syrup. Stir in flour mixture.
Add morsels. Drop by tablespoons onto greased baking sheets.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 12 minutes. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: cheese raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar.
Blend in vanilla.
Add cottage cheese and beat well.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until it is firm.
Cool to room temperature before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw and cut broccoli.
Cook rice.
Saute onion and celery in butter until soft.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in casserole and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix and pat into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt 1 large package chocolate chips.
Spread over and chill.
Cut into small pieces.

title: nacho dip
directions: Layer a 9 x 12-inch pan as follows:
refried beans, cream cheese, chunky salsa and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until cheese is bubbly.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients. Pour into 2 greased 9-inch pans and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and set aside to cool.
Mix cream cheese with a small amount of pineapple juice.
Add pineapple, cranberry sauce and chopped nuts, add to cooled gelatin mixture and chill until firm.

title: crunchy grouper
directions: You will need 6 brown paper bags.

title: sweet pea salad
directions: Mix green peas, onion and cheese.
Add mayonnaise.

title: super fruit salad
directions: Mix drained fruits together.
Mix pudding, milk and orange juice and beat together.
Beat in sour cream and pour over fruit and stir.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil until smooth.
Next, add the salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix well together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.
Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: garlic soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add chopped onions and garlic; saute for a few minutes.
Add cut up cooked potatoes; cook for 3 or 4 minutes. Remove from heat; puree through a blender.
If too thick, add a little water.
Boil 1 quart water.
Add 2 tablespoons chicken paste.
Add ingredients from blender.
Add basil and white pepper. Enjoy!
You may want to serve croutons on top of soup.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in shallow 9 x 11-inch baking dish. Mix rest of ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover dish with Saran Wrap.
Microwave on High for 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 9 minutes.
(Use caution when handling dish and removing wrap.)

title: chicken breast roll-ups
directions: Wash and chop green onions, using tops.
Set aside.
Pound out the four chicken breast halves between two sheets of wax paper until very thin, but not so thin they tear.
Spread each breast with mustard generously.
Place cheese on each breast and roll up, securing with toothpicks.
Start rolling with thinnest edge tucked in first.
Put flour in low-sided bowl and season with salt and pepper.
Roll each chicken breast in flour mixture to coat.
Heat electric skillet to 325° to 350° and add butter and oil.
Spread over bottom evenly.
Brown chicken breasts on all sides evenly. Chicken is cooked through when brown.
Remove roll-ups to a plate and put in low oven to keep warm while making sauce.
Add vermouth or wine to skillet and scrape up drippings.
Add onions, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Stir and continue to cook at 350° until cooks down to about half the volume and is the consistency of a sauce, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve chicken breast on top of, or beside a bed of rice.
Top generously with sauce.

title: sausage roll
directions: In skillet, brown sausage and then add onion and green pepper. Continue cooking slowly until onion and green pepper are soft. Drain off grease.
(I use a colander.) Put in a bowl and add the 2 cheeses.
Stir well to blend.
Roll out bread dough and spread on meat filling.
Roll up as for jelly roll sealing edges.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add flour, beating until smooth.
Slowly stir in dry whipped topping mix.
Bake in moderate oven until springs back to the touch.

title: pork chops sweet and sour
directions: In a paper bag, mix the first 5 ingredients.
Shake chops in this mixture.
Brown chops in melted shortening in a frying pan. Cover with pineapple juice, mixed with vinegar.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Cover; cook over low heat until chops are fork-tender, about 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, sugar, flour and nutmeg and beat until smooth.
Put rhubarb in pie shell and pour egg mixture over and dot with a little margarine.
Cover with lattice top.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples. Place in pie shell. Combine apple juice, cornstarch and spices in a microwavable dish. Cook in microwave on High for 3 minutes. Pour mixture over apples. Add the second pie crust to top of pie. Make 2 or 3 vents in top crust to let steam escape. Cook at 400° for 45 minutes to an hour or until golden brown.

title: stew
directions: Brown beef lightly, drain.
Combine all ingredients and simmer, covered, 1 hour.
(I usually add a little sugar and cook longer than 1 hour.)

title: dream bars
directions: Mix.
Put this mixture on top of baked mixture.
Return to oven and bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Cut while warm.

title: ham broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ham and cheese over broccoli. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Slowly pour over casserole and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla and nuts; work in flour, which has been sifted with cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape in rolls about 2 inches in diameter and wrap in waxed paper.
Chill.
Slice and bake as desired on greased cookie sheet at 425°, about 6 minutes.
(Using butter gives it better flavor.)

title: pizza rustica
directions: Enough for two shells for a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients, cut in lard until crumbly, then add water, until dough forms a small soft ball.
Knead with a small amount of flour, then roll out to fit pan.
Should make enough for a top and a bottom.

title: crabmeat mold
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Put soup on low heat until warm. Add gelatin.
Over low heat, stir until dissolved.
Add mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Mix until smooth. Add other ingredients, adding crabmeat last.
Pour into dish greased with mayonnaise. Serve with crackers.

title: country chicken and dumplings
directions: In large pot, simmer cut up stewing hen.
When hen is fully cooked, remove from pot (about 40 minutes).
Set aside until cooled enough to handle; debone hen and dispose of bones.
Set aside.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add other ingredients and mix by hand.
Grease muffin tins, fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mama's dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg and milk.
Mix quickly and drop by spoonfuls over simmering gravy.
Cover tightly and cook 12 to 15 minutes without removing lid.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Parboil or microwave unpeeled potatoes.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch foil-lined pan as follows:
potatoes (sliced), onion (sliced), margarine (several slices per layer).
Salt and pepper each layer. Pour milk over the layers.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix in order given. Spread in pan and bake at 350° until a toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: friendship pudding
directions: Take friendship and love; mix them with tenderness.
Blend thoroughly with loyalty.
Add hope and faith.
Sprinkle with forgiveness.
Serve daily with an abundance of laughter.
Serves a whole bunch of people.

title: 1 cup cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 13 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Place cake mix, oil, eggs, and oranges in a bowl.
Beat together 3 to 4 minutes.
Do not add any other moisture.
Place in 3 layers.
(Can use a Bundt pan.
After it cools, slice the cake in half.)
Bake at 350 degrees.
This will take 25 to 30 minutes for the layers or 50 minutes for the bundt pan.
Combine pineapple and pudding mix in a small bowl.
Fold in Cool Whip. Ice the layers.
If you use a bundt pan, after icing cake, fill the hole with the remaining icing.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Add oranges and mix all.
Pour into either 3 greased and floured cake pans or a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and stir into eggs.
Add milk and pumpkin.
Pour filling into pie shells.
Bake in very hot oven (450°) 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to slow (325°) and bake 35 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.

title: chicken marsala
directions: In large skillet, heat butter.
Brown garlic until golden and discard.
Saute chicken breasts in flavored butter until well browned on all sides.
Add mushrooms and Marsala.
Cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Remove chicken breasts to warm platter.
Over high heat, heat sauce in skillet to boiling, scraping up any brown bits from the bottom of the pan. Cook until sauce thickens slightly.
Stir in parsley and pour over.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Cut up peppers, seed and all (peppers are to taste).
Add soup, milk and peppers to cheese and heat in microwave on medium-high for 2 minutes.
Stir and reheat until completely melted and mixed.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler and paraffin wax.
Roll the first 4 ingredients into balls.
With toothpick, dunk balls into chocolate mixture.

title: apple dumpling
directions: Make syrup of sugar, water and cinnamon.
Add butter.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder; cut in shortening.
Add milk; stir until moistened.
Roll out on floured surface, 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 5-inch squares.
Place apples in each square; fold corners to center and pinch edges together.
Place in baking dish.
Pour syrup over dumplings.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Serve hot, plain or with ice cream.

title: scalloped onions and peas
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter. Stir in flour, mustard and salt; cook and stir until bubbly. Stir in milk and worcestershire sauce; cook and stir until thickened, about 2 minutes. Gently stir in onions, peas and almonds. Pour into an ungreased 2 qt. baking dish. Sprinkle with parmesan and paprika. Cover and bake at
350° for 30 minutes.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Mix and toss apples 1/2 c. sugar 2 Tbsp. flour and cinnamon. Place in pie shell and cover with mixture.
Cut together remaining sugar, remaining flour and oleo.
Place in brown paper bag and bake 1 hour at 425°.

title: mold scrub solution
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a clean gallon jug.
Add enough water to make 1 gallon.
Fill smaller spray bottles and use in showers, refrigerator seals, etc. or anywhere you have a mold problem.

title: sour cream waffles
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar; set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Beat egg yolks. Gradually add melted butter, sour cream add buttermilk.
Mix until smooth, then add flour mixture.
Gently fold in egg whites.
Makes 8 large or 12 small waffles.

title: chicken vegetable pasta salad
directions: In a medium bowl, with wire whisk, combine broth, mayonnaise, cheese and dill weed. In a large shallow nonmetallic dish, combine pasta, chicken, tomatoes, mushrooms, onion and chicken broth mixture; toss to coat. Cover; refrigerate until serving time, at least 4 hours, stirring occasionally. Serve on spinach and lettuce leaves. Makes 4 servings.

title: creamy sure fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter, Marshmallow Creme and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Cook until mixture has boiled for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add chocolate pieces and vanilla.
Stir until everything is melted, then stir in nuts. Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Let stand until firm; cut into squares.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds of candy.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Mix 3 cups of flour with salt and sugar; set aside.
Add sour cream to melted butter in a small saucepan.
Heat until mixture feels very warm to touch. Pour into a large bowl.
Add yeast and flour mixture.
Mix well. Add eggs and beat with a wooden spoon.
Add remaining flour, 1/2 cup at a time, to make soft dough.
Scrape dough down from sides and let rise until doubled.
Punch down.
Divide dough in half. Roll out each half to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into 2-inch rounds. Place on greased baking sheet.
Cover.
Let rise until doubled (about 30 minutes).
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: texas goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Saute onions and green peppers. Mix all ingredients in a saucepan with meat; simmer 15 minutes. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish.
Mix Jiffy following instructions on box.
Spread over meat mixture as a topping.
Bake at 350° until corn bread is golden brown.

title: low-fat carrot salad
directions: Cook raisins in little pineapple juice for 1 minute in microwave.
Combine all other ingredients.
Add raisins.
mix well.
If dry, pour a little orange juice over salad.
Will keep several days in the refrigerator.

title: carol's microwave potatoes
directions: Combine cornflakes, cheese and spices.
Roll potatoes in melted butter, then in crumbs.
Sprinkle extra crumbs over all. Microwave 10 to 12 minutes on High, covered.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, sugar, and salt.

Slowly add 1 cup of the cream, stirring with a rubber spatula, to form a smooth dough, Add up to 1/2 cup additional cream if mixture is too dry, being careful not to overwork the dough or the biscuits will be tough.

title: remote control casserole
directions: Pick meat off bones.
Mix together Ro-Tel and soups.
In crock-pot, layer crushed Doritos, half the chicken, half onion and half soup mixture, then 1/2 Velveeta cheese slices.
Layer all again, ending with Velveeta cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: baked mushroom chicken
directions: Place chicken, rib side down, in pan.
Drain liquid from a can of mushrooms and reserve.
Put mushrooms over chicken.
Mix the reserved liquid with the mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour the mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika or fresh ground pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or at 225° for up to 4 hours, covered.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into thick slices.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dip in cornmeal, pressing meal firmly onto slices.
Fry in bacon drippings, adding more if needed, until lightly browned. Drain on paper towels.
Serve at once.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: noodles with clam sauce
directions: Heat oil; add garlic and onion.
Saute 1 or 2 minutes. Remove; stir in clams, parsley, mushrooms, salt, pepper and pimentos.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
While sauce simmers, cook noodles according to package; drain.
Place in serving dish.
Stir in hot clam sauce.

title: oriental beef and peppers
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, ginger, garlic and 1/4 cup soy sauce.
Add meat and stir to coat well.
Let marinate 20 minutes. Mix together water, 2 teaspoons cornstarch and 1 tablespoon soy sauce; set aside.
In wok or frying pan, heat 2 tablespoons salad oil.
Add beef and marinade and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly 1 or 2 minutes or until beef is no longer pink.
Do not overcook.
Remove beef from pan.
Heat remaining 2 tablespoons salad oil in same pan.
Add green pepper, carrots and onion.
Cook, stirring constantly, until vegetables are tender, yet crisp, about 4 minutes.
Salt lightly.
Add beef, tomatoes and water mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and margarine in large, heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Pour over popped corn.
Mix thoroughly in large roaster.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: friend's spaghetti
directions: Mix all together, put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed until creamy.
Gradually add 3/4 cup powdered sugar, beating well.
Add flour, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls, place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove to wire racks to cool slightly. Roll warm cookies in additional powdered sugar.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Line 10 x 13-inch pan with bread.
Saute onion, celery and pepper in butter.
Combine with cooked chicken; add mayonnaise. Spread over layer of bread.
Top with another layer of bread.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over top.
Pour mushroom soup over next.
Top with grated cheese and paprika.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Bake uncovered.

title: pigs 'n' blanket
directions: Mix together last 2 ingredients.
Spread on bread.
Wrap around wiener.
Put toothpick to hold together.
Bake in oven at 375° until bread is slightly brown.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix flour and sour cream.
Melt butter and add slowly.
Place biscuits on ungreased cookie sheet and cook at 450° until lightly brown.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour half the batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
While cake is baking, combine oleo, condensed milk and caramels in microwave until smooth.
Add pecans.
Remove cake from oven and pour candy mixture evenly over candy.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: granola cereal
directions: Mix together dry ingredients except raisins, then add oil, water and vanilla; mix well.
Spread evenly on cookie sheets. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Add raisins after cooking.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Place sugar in bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in margarine and buttermilk.
Add vanilla and flour.
Add coconut and pecans.
Put in pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: strawberry torte
directions: Combine flour and 1 tablespoon of sugar; add melted margarine. Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until light brown; let cool.

title: two tone bites
directions: Over hot (not boiling) water, combine first 4 ingredients until melted and smooth.
Stir in peanuts.
Press into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften cream cheese and oleo; mix together with sugar.
Add eggs and flour, alternately 1 egg, 1/2 cup flour, etc.
Mix and add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in angel food cake pan.

title: berkshire pudding
directions: Mix sugar and butter until creamy.
Melt chocolate and add to creamed mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each egg is added.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Line pan with crushed graham crackers. Pour mixture into it and sprinkle top with crushed crackers.
Top with whipped cream and keep refrigerated.

title: apple custard pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients slightly, until apples cook up a little.
Beat eggs and add other ingredients, then add first mixture.
Place in pie crust and bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes, then at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes more.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Cut the bread into 1 1/2-inch rounds (4 per slice).
Place the bread rounds on baking sheets.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Combine the American cheese, onion, pepper and mayonnaise.
Remove bread rounds to a wire rack.
Increase oven temperature to 325°.
Spread a teaspoonful of cheese mixture on each bread round.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: ranch picnic potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all of the vegetables. Stir mustard into salad dressing. Pour over potato mixture and toss slightly. Cover and refrigerate several hours. Sprinkle with eggs and paprika.

title: vegetable soup (with meat)
directions: Salt and pepper meat and brown (not with flour).
Place meat in large soup pot with 1 quart water.
Cook until tender.
Add string beans; cook 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, okra, celery, carrots and rice.
Cook until potatoes are tender, but not mushy.
Add all other ingredients and cook a while longer.
Good for company. Serve with corn muffins.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in large bowl; set aside.
Bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa and water; pour over flour and sugar mixture. Add buttermilk, eggs (slightly beaten), vanilla and baking soda; mix well.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes; let cool 5 minutes.
Prick top of cake with fork.
Pour icing over the cake.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
In another bowl, sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cut the pineapple, cherries and raisins in small pieces.
Add the flour mixture to the butter mixture saving a cup of flour to coat the fruit so it won't stick together.
Put all together after fruit is coated, then add the nuts.
Roll into rolls on wax paper and refrigerate until firm. Can be frozen for several months until ready to make.
Slice 1/4 inch each, bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
I use parchment cooking paper.
After first baking, others may take less time. Don't get them too brown.

title: donut muffins
directions: Beat egg with fork; add oil and milk and beat with fork.
Add dry ingredients to mixture and stir lightly with fork.
Place in muffin tins.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon and add dot of butter to each.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Combine in bowl chocolate cake mix, sour cream, eggs, oil, chocolate pudding, warm water and liqueur.
Stir to blend, then beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Turn into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until cake tests done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cinnamon, mixed together.
Will make 24 slices.

title: garden harvest casserole
directions: Mix vegetables together and place in a shallow 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle parsley and pepper over all.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour bouillon into a small saucepan.
Add oil, salt, tarragon and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling; adjust seasonings to taste.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover baking dish with aluminum foil.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are just tender and are still colorful.
Carefully stir vegetables occasionally, but to preserve color, don't lift cover off for long.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Cook noodles.
Add noodles, corn and tomato soup with hamburger.
Put in baking dish.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
While hot, put in 1 can whole cranberries and stir.
While this sits, prepare apples and nuts. Add crushed pineapple to the Jell-O and cranberries.
Mix and put in bowl to set.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips and cheese.
Best to make a day ahead.
Put cheese and chips on top before baking at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be served cold.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine ingredients; spread on pizza pan.
Top with cheese, lettuce, pepper, onion and tomatoes.
Onion can be optional. Serve with taco chips to dip.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Serve with cherries, bananas, cantaloupe, pineapple, strawberries or your favorite fruit. Delicious!

title: flaky biscuits(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together into mixing bowl.
Pour oil and milk together and add to flour mixture.
Mix and pour out on floured surface.
Knead about 10 times.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with medium-size cutter and bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, in boiling water to cover, 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain, let cool to touch.
Peel and cut into strips or squares.
Set aside.
Combine 1/4 cup margarine and next 5 ingredients in a large bowl; gently stir in potatoes and cheese. Spoon into a lightly greased baking dish.
Combine 3 tablespoons margarine and stuffing mix; sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: aunt betty's potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put in a greased 9 x 13 pan. Top with 1 cup crushed potato chips. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: corny chicken
directions: Wash and pat chicken dry.
Drop pieces into corn and roll into bread crumbs, coating each piece well.
Place chicken in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: orange pineapple punch
directions: In a punchbowl, stir together canned milk and pineapple juice.
Add orange soda.
Top with sherbet and serve over ice.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Beat
together	until
mixed
well.
Can
be
basted on partially cooked meats or poultry.	It can also be served with crackers and cream cheese.

title: cream cheese clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Then sprinkle heavily with Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: haynes' okra gumbo
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in large nonstick frying pan and stir frequently so the juice from the okra will dry up, leaving the ingredients non slimy.
This takes about 20 minutes, then add powder garlic, dill weed and salt.

title: egg and mushroom casserole
directions: Place eggs
in
quart
casserole; mix soup with eggs. Add
3/4 of cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter;
sprinkle remaining crumbs
on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
This is a good dish
to serve for brunch along with Canadian bacon, hot fruit dish, grits and rolls, champagne or coffee.

title: simple granola
directions: Preheat oven to 250 degrees.
Combine in a large mixing bowl flour, oatmeal, and coconut.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add cold water and lemonade.
Mix well.
Pour in pineapple juice.
Freeze punch mixture in a gallon container until slushy.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in a 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan. Let cake cool.
Poke holes all over cake with a fork.
Mix condensed milk with caramel topping together in a bowl until thoroughly blended.
Pour over cake.
Wait until cake absorbs the topping, then top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed candy.

title: emma's butterscotch candy
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels. Add peanuts and noodles. Drop with a spoon on waxed paper. Let cool before removing from paper. Makes 35.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Top with 2 slices of diced bacon and 1 cup of crusted Post Toasties.
Bake 1 hour in a 400° oven.

title: poppy seed chocolate chip nut bread
directions: Beat together first six ingredients.
Stir in last three ingredients.
Pour into greased bread pans and bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: french crepes
directions: Mix all together with a wire whip.
Fry as you would a pancake.
Drain on paper towel.
Cool.
Use whipped cream and top with fresh strawberries or blueberries.
Arrange the whipped cream on half of the crepe.
Then top with fresh fruit.
Then flip the crepe on top of fruit.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Heat 2 cups of the milk in a heavy saucepan.
In mixing bowl mix sugar, cornstarch, 1/2 cup of the milk and the egg yolks. Stir into steaming hot milk and cook until thick.
Add the butter and coconut.
Stir and put into baked pie shell and top with your favorite meringue.

title: creole gumbo
directions: Boil the chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones and cut in bite size pieces.
Set aside.
Make gravy with oil and flour in a large pot.
Add chopped celery, onion, green pepper and garlic to gravy.
Cook on low until tender.
Fry okra until tender.
Add to gravy mixture.
Add chicken, chicken broth, Worcestershire sauce, catsup, tomatoes and pepper flakes.
Simmer 3 hours.
Add shrimp. Simmer 30 minutes longer.
Add tablespoon of lemon juice, if desired.
Serve over rice.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook whole chicken; debone.
Save broth. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook noodles in chicken broth (may have to add more water).
Add noodles to top of chicken.
Add enough broth from noodles to make chicken look "soupy." Put the cream of mushroom soup on top; spread evenly.
Add the Cheddar cheese; top with crushed cracker crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream oleo, peanut butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Shape into balls about 1-inch in diameter. Roll balls in a little sugar and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for about 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and press chocolate candy kiss on each.
Return to oven to bake 2 to 5 minutes more or until brown.

title: party chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wrap each breast with sliced bacon. Cover bottom of greased 8 x 12-inch baking pan with beef.
Lay chicken on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over top of chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onions onto bottom of lightly greased pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: spinach cannelloni or ravioli filling
directions: Cook spinach according
to
package
directions.
Drain well until almost dry.
In
skillet melt butter and add onion. Saute for 2 to 3 minutes, remove from heat and add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Place
tablespoons
of spinach filling down center of
each
dried
pasta
square.
Fold
the opposite edges together over
filling
to
form a tube.
Place cannelloni in baking dish with a single layer of tomato sauce, sprinkled with Parmesan
cheese.
Repeat
until all cannelloni are formed.
Spoon more tomato
sauce on top of cannelloni and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake
to 25 minutes, until starts to bubble.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 15 to 20 cannelloni.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Sift the first 7 ingredients together.
Cream the butter and sugar in a bowl.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix the raisins, nuts and candied fruits with flour mixture.
Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the boiling hot applesauce.
Pour into a large tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: teriyaki sauce marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate chicken, steak or pork chops for 4 hours.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Put jalapeno dip on a 10 x 12-inch platter.
Mix avocados, lemon juice, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper; put it over the bean dip.
Mix sour cream, taco seasoning and mayonnaise; put over avocado mixture.
Cut up green onions, tops and all; put over sour cream mixture.
Cut up tomato, chopped and drained; put on top of green onions.
Drain sliced olives and layer over tomatoes.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serve as appetizer or with Spanish meal.

title: black-eyed peas mexican style
directions: Combine onion, garlic and bacon.
Cook until bacon is brown. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Warm vinegar and oil to dissolve sugar and other spices.
Pour over vegetables.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into bread pans. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Boil Karo and sugar, just until it comes to a boil.
Turn off and add peanut butter and cereal.
Shape into balls.

title: tender roast beef with gravy
directions: In center of 1 large sheet of foil, place roast.
Add soups (undiluted) and soup mix on top.
Seal foil tightly and place in a 325° oven for about 3 to 4 hours (depending on size of roast).

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large frypan.
Saute onion until clear. Reserve 3 tablespoons of cracker crumbs for topping.
Place remaining crumbs in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer onions and soup, alternating until full.
Combine eggs
and milk. Pour over onions and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut thin slice from stem end of each pepper.
Remove all seeds and membranes.
Wash inside and outside. Heat 1 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt until it comes to a boil, then add peppers and cook 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: amaretto punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water; stir in remaining ingredients.
Divide mixture evenly into 6-quart size, heavy-duty, Ziploc bags.
Freeze.
Reach each bag from freezer as needed.
Let stand at room temperature until mixture is slushy.
Yield:
about 6 quarts.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on micro-serving plate.
Spread chili on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter (or margarine), pat rice into melted butter.
Mix next 3 ingredients and pour over the rice and butter (or margarine).
Place chicken in mixture (already in casserole dish) and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Bake in oven 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Fry meat until brown and bubbly. Add onion, cooking for 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients in a large stew pot and cook for 1 hour. Top with grated Monterey Jack cheese and serve with toasted garlic to taste.

title: deana eger's banana-split cake
directions: Mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 5 minutes at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into small pieces and roll in 2/3 cup sugar plus 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Place coated biscuits in buttered Bundt pan. Combine butter, 2/3 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 teaspoon vanilla in saucepan.
Bring to boil and pour over biscuits.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
When cool, unmold onto plate.

title: fruity party punch
directions: Prepare the lemonade and orange juice as directed on cans. Combine orange juice, lemonade, pineapple juice, and cranberry juice in a large mixing bowl or pitcher. Chill. Immediately before serving add ice cubes.

title: cream of cabbage soup
directions: Cut cabbage very fine.
