Add boiling water and cook until soft, then press through a sieve and return to liquor. Melt butter. Add onion and simmer for 3 minutes.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and cayenne.
Add milk and cabbage mixture gradually, stirring constantly.
Strain. Reheat and serve hot garnished with cheese balls or puffs.

title: cabbage roll-ups
directions: Trim base of cabbage and carefully break off 8 whole leaves. (Save remaining cabbage to cook for a vegetable or make into salad for another meal.)

title: freezer corn
directions: Wash ears uncooked.
Cut off, then cook on medium-low heat until starts to boil, then cook for 10 minutes.
Let cool and put into boxes or bags and freeze.

title: cheese-pumpkin soup
directions: In large, heavy saucepan, lightly saute green onions in butter.
Stir in flour, seasoned salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Remove from heat.
Add milk and chicken broth.
Cook, stirring, about 15 minutes, until thickened.
Blend in pumpkin.
Simmer 5 minutes longer, stirring frequently.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Top each serving, if desired, with a slice of tomato, sprinkled with cheese and green onions (optional).

title: overnight luncheon dish
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: colorful holiday salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Heat the next 4 ingredients and pour over vegetable mixture; mix well. Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 6.

title: cream cheese fruit cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients and bake for 15 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble and cook 5 more minutes.
Save 1/4 cup of crust mixture.

title: microwave international meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish (browning dish).
Bake with microwave on Medium 6 to 8 minutes or until completely cooked.
Turn meatballs over once about halfway through the cooking time.
Place meatballs in serving dish, reserving drippings for later use.
Serve meatballs plain or with sauces.
Makes 25 to 30 meatballs.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into cupcake liners and bake at 325°.
Variation:
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or in 3 little loaf pans for 45 minutes.

title: col. sanders' pecan pie
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Place 2/3 cup pecan halves in an unbaked pie shell.
Pour in the above mixture. Bake 35 minutes in 325° to 350° oven.

title: eggplant neptune(eggplant in clam sauce)
directions: In a cured, heavy iron skillet put margarine and the liquid from the cans of chopped clams.
Add the pressed garlic and cook slowly.
Put the cubed eggplant into the clam juice and cook, stirring from time to time, for about 15 minutes.
Add the first 1/4 cup minced parsley and the minced chives and cook for 5 minutes more.
Add the chopped clams, grated Parmesan and the remaining 1/4 cup of fresh parsley.
Mix well and serve at once.
Do not overcook!

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and add garlic powder to taste; chill. Serve with crackers.
Can be frozen.
May also roll in chopped nuts.

title: shrimp etouffee(serves 4 to 6)
directions: In a skillet, melt butter and stir in flour.
Cook, stirring constantly, until this is a rich brown color.
Add vegetables and cook until tender.
Stir in water, shrimp, parsley and seasonings. Simmer, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes or until shrimp are done. Do not overcook.
Serve over hot rice.

title: thank you strawberries
directions: Boil together Danish
Dessert
and water and add sliced strawberries and sugar.
Boil
for 2 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Can be used on top of angel food cake or puddings.

title: turnip greens and ham hock
directions: Wash ham hocks and place in an 8-quart Dutch oven.
Add water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 30 to 40 minutes, or until tender.
Pick and wash turnip greens.
Peel turnip roots; cut in half.
Add greens, roots, salt and sugar to Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for about 30 to 45 minutes, or until greens and roots are tender.

title: monogamy cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add egg yolks and beat thoroughly. Sift flour; measure and sift with soda, salt and cocoa.
Combine sifted ingredients and sour milk with first mixture.
Add dates and nuts, which have been dredged in 2 tablespoons of flour.
Mix thoroughly; fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes two nine-inch layers.

title: frog-eye salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Gradually stir in the pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring until thickened.
Add lemon juice; cool mixture to room temperature.
Bring water, remaining salt and oil to a boil.
Add acini de pepe; cook at a rolling boil until done.
Drain and rinse with water; drain again and cool to room temperature.
Combine egg mixture and acini de pepe.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly. Refrigerate overnight in airtight container.
Be sure to drain canned fruit.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Refrigerate until chilled in airtight container. Will keep for up to a week.

title: five hour stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a large baking kettle or ovenproof Dutch oven.
Mix and cover.
If you like to add more meat or vegetables, go ahead.
They won't hurt the stew.
Place in a 250° oven for five hours.
Don't open the oven or take off the pot lid to see how the stew's coming.
In other words, no peeking until time is up.
Serve with fresh hot bread or cornbread and baked apples stuffed with brown sugar, cinnamon and butter.
This is one meal that's even more delicious as a leftover.

title: delicious microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in a bowl.
Arrange this mixture in a donut shape in glass pie plate.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at Medium 10 minutes.
(Rotate pie plate 1/2 turn for 5 minutes if your microwave doesn't have a carousel.) Next, remove drippings and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 6 to 8 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Stir
together ingredients.
Freeze for 3 days.
Thirty minutes before
serving,
place in punch bowl and add 2 quarts ginger ale.
Or
for
individual enjoyment, place a scoop or 2 in a glass and add ginger ale.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Beat egg yolks, shortening and margarine until well blended. Gradually add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add extracts and blend.
Beat in flour with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add coconut and blend.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold whites into batter.

title: bonnie bennett's fudge
directions: Boil sugar, butter and cream to soft ball stage.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir continuously until thick.
Place in 1 or 2 large pans and cut.
Makes a very large amount.

title: vermont maple baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
In the morning, parboil the beans until the skins crack when blown upon.
Cut onion in quarters and put in bottom of bean pot.
Add parboiled beans.
Mix the sugar, syrup, mustard, pepper and salt with 1 pint of boiling water.
Pour this over the beans and salt pork.
If necessary, add more boiling water to cover.
Bake at 300° for 6 hours or more, adding more boiling water as the beans cook.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage up and cook in water until tender.
Drain.
In a large casserole dish put a layer of cabbage, dot with margarine. Mix the chicken soup, milk and cheese.
Pour half of this mixture over the first layer of cabbage.
Put another layer of cabbage and the rest of the mixture, dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: finger jello
directions: Boil mix with top ingredients.
Cool and cut.

title: cherry-cranberry jello salad
directions: Add hot, then cold water to jello.
When dissolved, add cranberries immediately.
When cool, add celery and nuts. Refrigerate.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Mix and beat 4 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: herb chicken and gravy
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour and sage.
Coat chicken lightly with flour mixture.
In skillet over medium-high heat, in hot margarine, cook chicken until browned on both sides.
Add soup and 1/2 cup water, stirring to loosen browned bits.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: roast beef with penne pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Cut roast beef into strips.
Saute garlic, peppers and onions in olive oil until tender.
Combine roast beef strips with all ingredients and toss. Serve warm or cold.

title: orange muffins
directions: Mix well until all is dissolved.
Spoon over muffins as soon as they come out of oven.
Makes up to 32 muffins.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Put rice in baking dish.
Place chicken breasts on rice. Cover with Lipton soup mix. Add 2 cans asparagus soup plus 2 cans of water.
Cover and bake for 2 hours at 250°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add vanilla, salt and soda; mix.
Add flour; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hello dollies
directions: Combine crumbs and butter.
Press in the bottom of long baking dish.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Cover with nuts.
Place coconut on top.
Stripe with milk.
Cook for 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Let cool before cutting into bars.

title: chicken dijon
directions: In skillet, in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown and remove.
In an additional 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook onion until tender.
Stir often.
Add soup, milk, mustard and parsley.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes.

title: brussels sprouts with cream and garlic
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts in large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain, rinse under cold water and drain again.
(Can be prepared 1 day ahead and refrigerated.)
Melt butter in heavy large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic and cook until soft, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.
Do not brown.
Add Brussels sprouts, cream, salt and pepper and cook until cream thickens enough to coat Brussels sprouts, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes.
Serve hot. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: inez's sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain kraut, cut into 1-inch pieces.
Place in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Let sit for 24 hours.

title: ice cream icing
directions: Mix ingredients all together and beat until light and fluffy.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add cocoa and food coloring.
Sift flour and salt together. Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Sprinkle soda and then vinegar over batter and stir until well blended. Add vanilla and pour into 2 (9-inch) cake pans, greased and floured.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate italian cream cake
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix together flour, cocoa, salt and soda.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Bake in three 9-inch cake pans (greased and floured). Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook amount of noodles desired.
Each noodle makes one roll-up. Drain noodles.
When cool enough to handle, make roll-ups as follows:
Lay noodle flat.
In the middle of each noodle, place a folded slice of ham and a folded slice of cheese.
Fold each end of the noodle over the middle.
Pour half of the sauce in the bottom of baking pan.
Place noodle rolls, with folded side down, in sauce.
Pour remaining sauce on top of noodles and sprinkle with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: horned dorset dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, uncovered.
Enjoy with your favorite cracker.

title: colored popcorn balls
directions: Combine marshmallows and margarine in saucepan.
Stir over medium-low heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin. Pour over popcorn.
Stir to coat.
Using buttered hands, form into balls.
Store in individual Ziploc bags.
Great for kids to help make!!

title: yogurt cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla. Mix or beat until smooth. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 1 small cake.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream the butter; add powdered sugar and milk.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Drop on waxed paper.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: albert's mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onion.
Drain off all grease.
Add soup and hot sauce.
Line bottom of casserole dish with 1/2 package of crushed Doritos.
Add layer of grated cheese.
Pour in meat mixture and top with remaining Doritos and grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: holiday punch
directions: Add water to orange juice and lemonade according to package directions.
Pour all ingredients into punch bowl; stir to mix. Add ice cubes and serve.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: all day pork chops
directions: Dredge chops in flour, granules and dry mustard.
Brown in oil in a large skillet.
Place the browned chops in a crock-pot.
Add undiluted chicken and rice soup and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours. Don't forget to add the diced onion.
Salt and chicken granules may be omitted if so desired.

title: louisiana green beans
directions: Cook beans until tender, then add remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat until cooked through, about 15 minutes. Serves 8.

title: pretzel fried chicken
directions: Dry chicken with paper towels. Combine eggs and milk in a large bowl.
Place pretzel crumbs in a large bag.
Dip chicken in milk mixture, then place in bag with pretzel crumbs and shake until coated well. Fry chicken in 350° oil until golden brown (approximately 10 minutes per side).
Wrap pieces in aluminum foil and place in baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes until done.

title: chicken tamale pie
directions: Add 1/2 cup cheese to cornbread mix and prepare as directed. Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix chicken, soup, seasoning, pimiento and water in saucepan and heat until warm.
Spoon cornbread mixture into greased 2-quart casserole.
Spoon chicken mixture over cornbread to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes.
Top with cheese while hot.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows, add milk, raisins, cherries and pecans. Mix in cracker crumbs and pack into foil lined cracker box. Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil spaghetti until tender.
Rinse in cold water.
Grease baking dish and put butter in dish.
Place in oven just until melted.
Take out and layer with noodles, cheese, salt and pepper. Repeat and dot top with butter, paprika, salt and pepper.
Pour warm milk to 1/2 inch of top.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then lower to 350° and bake until done, about 30 minutes.

title: mark's pasta with zucchini
directions: In large pan, saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add ham, pepperoncini, salt and parsley.
Saute over medium heat for a few minutes.
Add zucchini and cook until zucchini is very limp, stirring frequently.
Add butter.

title: tomato and pasta soup
directions: Put all the ingredients, except pasta, into a saucepan and cook for 30 minutes.
Force through a sieve and bring again to a boil.
Add pasta and continue cooking for about 10 minutes.

title: light ambrosia cheesecake
directions: In a small bowl, mix crumbs, 1/4 coconut and margarine.
Press in bottom of an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Chill for 1 hour.
In a small saucepan over high heat, bring pineapple juice to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add the gelatin.
Mix well; cool to lukewarm. In a medium mixing bowl, using an electric mixer set on high speed, beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Beat in coconut extract and cooled gelatin mixture.
Pour in prepared crust; cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: In 3-quart pan, fry bacon to crisp.
Add onion; cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Add water and potato cubes; simmer until potatoes are tender.
Stir in soup, milk, salt, pepper and parsley.
Heat to serve (do not boil).

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Sift together next 4 ingredients.
Stir into first mixture.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll these in mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Place 2-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned, but still soft.
(The cookies will puff up at first.)

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in baking dish.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Heat oil in frying pan.
Add chicken and cook, turning until golden brown (about 10 minutes).
Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine onion, catsup, lemon juice, soy sauce, sugar, pepper and 1/2 cup water; blend well.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Bring to a boil all ingredients, then add 1 box confectioners sugar and beat.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in hot water, 1 1/2 minutes in microwave.
Mix together next 6 ingredients (separate eggs; beat whites until very stiff and set aside).
Add chocolate, buttermilk and flour.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Fold in sour cream, mixing well.
Preheat skillet and pour in mixture and bake until a golden brown.
Let cool about 5 minutes before cutting to serve.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese, adding milk and lemon juice.
Stir in flavor.
Pour into pie pan.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Top with your favorite fruit.

title: oven pot roast
directions: Dredge roast in flour and pepper; brown in butter in a Dutch oven.
Combine soups and liquid; pour over roast.
Cover; bake in a 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Add mushrooms.
Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: pea salad
directions: Thaw peas and pat dry.
Chop egg, pickles, celery and cauliflower.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix mayonnaise with powdered Ranch mix.
Add black olives if desired.
Sprinkle cheese and mix.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Combine tea, cinnamon sticks, cloves, orange peel, lemon peel and boiling water.
Allow to steep for 20 minutes.
Remove tea. Add remaining ingredients; heat through.
Yields 6 cups.

title: my dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch ovenproof dish.
Dump in the undrained pineapple; swirl it around and fill all corners.
Dump in cherry pie filling to cover the pineapple.
Dump the cake mix over the cherries and sprinkle the nuts.
Cut margarine into patties and lay over top.
Pop the whole thing in a 350° oven and bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: ramen chicken salad
directions: Mix cabbage, onion, chicken, noodles (uncooked and crumbled), oil, sugar, rice vinegar, salt, pepper and noodle seasoning; stir well and toss.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, garnish with sesame seeds and almonds.
Serves 8.

title: mama's forgotten chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place rice in bottom of shallow, greased baking pan. Combine cream soups and water. Pour half of the mixture over rice; let stand a few minutes. Place chicken pieces on top of rice and soup; salt and pepper. Rub chicken pieces with butter. Pour remaining cream soup mixture over chicken and top with dry onion soup mix. Add sliced onion over this, if desired. Cover with foil and forget about it for 1 hour and 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: my mother's three egg cake
directions: Mix everything together until lumps are gone.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Great for making jelly cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Place pecans in pastry shell.
In a large bowl, stir the first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Pour over pecans (pecans will rise to top).
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Cool.
Serves 8.

title: california casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onion in oil.
Add meat and brown.
Add salt, pepper, chili powder and mustard (to taste).
Add other ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Put cheese on top and bake for 10 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken roll-ups
directions: Saute onion and pepper in small amount of
oil. Add this to the chicken. Add sour cream and cheese.
Mix well.
Flatten each biscuit and add a teaspoonful of chicken mixture.
Roll up biscuit and put all biscuits on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 400° until browned.
Add soup and milk in saucepan and heat. Pour over biscuits in casserole dish and bake 30 minutes longer at 350°.

title: barley soup
directions: Put meat in kettle and add water to cover.
It is better to start with more water and let it cook away than to add water later on.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, and continue cooking, skimming occasionally until meat is half done.
Add diced vegetables, garlic, bay leaf, chicken instant broth and potatoes and simmer until meat is tender.
Cook the pearl barley separately, adding half the butter.
When meat and potatoes are done, remove bones and add barley.
Bring to a boil.
Check the seasoning.
Brown the flour in the butter or margarine until light brown (add a little of the soup liquid, stirring constantly and thicken the soup with the mixture.
Add chopped parsley and dill.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in shallow roasting pan. Cover with cherry filling.
Pour dry cake mix over.
Sprinkle with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: rice dessert
directions: Stir together all ingredients and chill.

title: party snacks
directions: Fry hamburger, pork sausage and onion until well done.
Pour off grease.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Cheez Whiz, oregano, garlic powder and sugar.
Mix until cheese is melted.
Put on rye slices.
Arrange on foil-lined cookie sheets.
May be frozen. When ready to serve, heat in 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Saute onions, green pepper and garlic in melted butter.
Add meat and cook until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add other ingredients and simmer slowly 3 to 4 hours.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in pumpkin.
Beat eggs well and add with milk to the mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top and bake at 375° for 10 minutes and 350° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted from edge of pie comes out clean. Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Beat cream cheese; add sour cream and seasoning.
Fold into potatoes.
Spoon 1/2 into casserole; top with cheese slices.
Add remaining potatoes and top with cheese. Bake about 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until hot through and cheese melts.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Thoroughly mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Combine milk, water and margarine.
Heat until just warm.
Slowly add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Add egg and 1 cup flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Scrape bowl.
Add enough flour to make stiff batter.
Spoon into 2 well-greased coffee cans (1 pound size).
Cover with plastic lids.
Let rise until almost to top of can.
Remove lids and bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Remove from cans and cool on rack on side.

title: "aunt betty's" snow drop cookies
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together; set aside.
Combine eggs, milk, oil and lemon extract.
Add sugar, then flour, a little at a time.
Roll in small balls.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
When cool, frost and add jimmies or confetti candies.

title: shirley's cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion tips and ham; refrigerate.
Serve with variety of crackers.
(Can use light cream cheese.)

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the pudding and milk together with mixer for two minutes. Fold in the sour cream and whipped topping. Layer the mixture with the vanilla wafers and bananas. Store in the refrigerator. Makes a lot. Serves 8 to 12.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place English muffins, crust side down, on a cookie sheet. Spread each

muffin half with 2 tablespoons pizza sauce. Top sauce with green pepper, mushrooms and onion. Sprinkle each muffin half with 2 tablespoons shredded cheese. Put on cookie sheet in oven. Bake 5 minutes. Bake until cheese is bubbling. Baking time might vary. Makes 4 small pizzas.

title: saucepan raisin spice bars
directions: Rub bottom of cookie sheet with margarine.

title: hash brown omelet
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of fat.
Crumble bacon.
Set aside.

title: broccoli casserole #2
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix egg, soup and cheese.
Pour over broccoli.
Pour 3 cups cracker crumbs over broccoli and soup.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple, luau style
directions: Remove leafy top of pineapple and reserve.
Cut pineapple lengthwise into 8
wedges.
Cut
off
core
of each wedge, then slash vertically
1-inch
apart
down
to but not through skin. Heat butter
in
small
saucepan on grill until melted. Add honey, lime
juice
and
ginger.
Brush
cut
surfaces
of pineapple with the lime
juice.
Place spears on the grill for 15 minutes, turning every 5 minutes and brushing with the lime mixture.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Cut 1 1/2-inches from the top of a ready baked angel food cake.
Set aside.
Mix 2 boxes instant chocolate pudding with a large Cool Whip thoroughly.
Pour over the mixture the second half of the cake.
Place the remaining portion on top and cover the entire cake.
Chill and serve.

title: crustless pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour into a greased pie plate and bake for 50 to 55 minutes.
Yields 1 pie.

title: round steak rolls
directions: Roll out crackers to make crumbs; add chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Cut steak into 4 x 6-inch pieces.
Fill with cracker mixture and a strip of ham fat or a piece of bacon, cut about 1-inch thick.
Roll and hold together with toothpicks.
The ham fat makes a moist dressing.
Brown steak rolls in a heavy frying pan.
Add a little water and simmer about 1 hour.
Add more water if necessary.
If you have any cracker crumbs left over, put into pan when steak is done to thicken sauce......(makes a nice gravy).

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir 1/2 hot mixture into egg yolks.
Then blend into hot mixture in saucepan and boil 1 minute more, stirring constantly.

title: peanut butter cookies(sugarless)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased pan.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 42 cookies.

title: kool-aid jelly
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
except
sugar in large saucepan. Bring to rolling boil, then add sugar all at once.
Cook to an active boil that cannot be stirred down, 1 or 2 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars; seal immediately.
Yields 2 1/2 pints.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in 1 stick oleo.
After rice is almost done, add broccoli and mix well.
Add cheese and soups to onion, celery and pepper.
Mix well.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried oysters
directions: Shuck oysters.
Throw in crumbs.
Throw in frying pan and saute in butter.
Delicious!

title: pork chops and apples
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown pork chops on both sides in hot fat. Place apples in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Top with pork chops.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: classic mexican beans - garay's version(these beans contain less fat than the canned versions)
directions: Pick over, wash and drain beans.
Place in 6 to 8-quart Dutch oven and cover with water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer until tender (2 to 3 hours).
Add boiling water whenever needed to keep beans barely covered.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together; add eggs.
Blend well. Mix all dry ingredients.
Add 1/2 of flour mixture to sugar, butter and egg mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Add milk, gradually, and vanilla.
Mix until batter is smooth.
Add remaining flour mixture and mix until smooth.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Add bananas and dry ingredients, milk, vanilla and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef-a-roni
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix ground beef, chopped green pepper and chopped onion.
Brown in a large skillet.
Drain well.
Cook macaroni according to package and drain well.
Mix macaroni, tomato paste and meat mixture together.

title: unfried french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice potatoes lengthwise into 1/4-inch ovals, then slice each oval lengthwise into matchstick size slices.
Spray baking sheet with 3 sprays Pam.
Mix egg whites and Cajun Spice together.
Add potatoes and mix to coat.
Put single layer potatoes on baking sheet.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes on bottom rack until crispy.
Turn with spatula every 6 to 8 minutes.

title: olive craver's bread pudding
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Sprinkle the top with cinnamon and some of the brown sugar.
Dot with oleo.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil chicken about 1 hour; debone.
Mix remaining ingredients with chicken.
Put in baking dish; top with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain all fruit good; cut in small pieces except oranges.
Mix real good; let it set overnight in refrigerator.

title: texas millionaires(candies)
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Cool.
Enjoy!

title: rhubarb crumb pie
directions: Mix together flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, cinnamon and butter until crumbly.
Put 1/2 of the crumb mixture into pastry lined 9-inch pan, reserving 1/2 of crumb mixture to put on top.
Cover with rhubarb.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all together. Make into balls.

title: louisiana cornbread
directions: Mix eggs, oil and water together.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9x13 pan. Cook for 35-40 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Boil fryer until done
and debone into bite size pieces ahead of time.
Combine
soup, milk, cheese and peppers into a mixture. Layer a
casserole	dish with Doritos, chicken, then sauce; repeat.
Top with Doritos.	Bake
at
350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fajita pie
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Cook and stir meat, vegetables and garlic powder in hot oil in large skillet until browned.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: old english trifle
directions: You can cut calories by using light pound cake, pineapple in own juices, skim milk in pudding and light Cool Whip.

title: creamy cheesecake
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and sugar together.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie crust.
Top with strawberries or cherries. Keep refrigerated.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt margarine over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard and pepper until smooth.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat for about 8 minutes, or until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Put macaroni in a 2-quart dish.
Pour cheese mixture over macaroni; mix well.
Combine the rest of cheese and bread crumbs. Sprinkle over cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 23 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift together 1 1/8 cups sugar, cocoa, flour and cornstarch. In a 2-quart boiler, mix milk, condensed milk, water and butter or margarine.
Separate eggs and slightly beat yolks.
Mix all ingredients and cook over low heat.
Add vanilla.
Stir constantly. Pour into baked 9 or 10-inch pie shell.

title: pioneer johnnycake
directions: Beat
eggs until light.
Add buttermilk and molasses or honey. Combine
dry
ingredients
and
stir into batter along with melted butter.
Pour into buttered dripper pan to bake at 425° for about
minutes
or
until
done.
Cut into large squares to serve.
Makes 24 pieces.

title: greek rice pudding
directions: Simmer rice in milk for about 45 minutes or until it thickens and rice is soft.
Beat eggs well.
Beat sugar into eggs. Gradually stir rice mixture into beaten eggs and sugar mixture. Mix well.
Return to cooking pan.
Add salt and cook over low heat about 2 more minutes.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread frozen potatoes across pan.
Salt and pepper, if desired.
Chop onion and crumble on top next, then spread all the cheese over evenly.
Pour whipping cream over top.
Drizzle melted butter around.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
(Cover with foil first 1/2 hour or so, then remove foil and continue baking until cheese is melted and golden brown.) May be made ahead and frozen.

title: grandma's raisin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine raisins and water in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in oil.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in sugar and egg.
Sift together dry ingredients and beat into raisin mixture.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until done.
When cool, cut into bars.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pie shells.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Put other pie shell over the top and seal.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind fruits. Add sugar and mix.
Prepare jello with 1 1/2 cups hot water and add 1 1/4 cups cold water.
Mix all ingredients and chill.
May garnish with mayonnaise.
Fills two 13 x 15-inch Pyrex dishes.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: diet chick(good enough for company)
directions: First:
Boil 1/4 of the chicken strips with celery and whole onion in 1-quart of water.

Save broth. Then use 1 cup of broth to cook garlic and onions (microwave suggested). Brown remaining chicken strips in skillet sprayed with Pam. Pour all remaining ingredients, including as much broth as pan can hold.
Stir and gently cook until peppers are tender.
Adjust flavors.
Too lemony?
Add soy sauce.
Serve over linguine or any pasta or rice. Yields 6 servings.

title: hot chili(not too hot, just good)
directions: Brown meat in large pot.
Stir in onion and celery (I cook this for a few minutes).
Stir in tomatoes.
Add chili and garlic powder.
Add beans.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
This makes 4 servings.

title: mixed vegetables baked
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Brown onion.
Add milk and cheese. Cut up and mix well.
Put in a casserole.
Cover with crushed crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers and remove tops and seeds.
Place peppers in casserole and set aside.
Next take ground meat, in a saucepan, add onion, salt, pepper, garlic, and brown.
Then add tomato sauce, and rice.
Take mixture and put into peppers.
Cook in 350° oven until brown approximatley 20 minutes.

title: graham cracker delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place graham crackers on ungreased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Melt the butter and sugar over low heat in a saucepan.
When melted, stir constantly for 2 minutes (no longer).
Remove from heat and add pecans.
Spread evenly over the graham crackers.

title: crab quesadillas
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix crab, cheese, onions, chiles and jalapeno.
Place 5 tortillas in a single layer on 2 large baking sheets.
Cover with crab mixture; top with remaining tortillas. Bake 7 to 9 minutes, until cheese is melted and tortillas are lightly browned.
Cut in wedges.
Serve hot with salsa and sour cream.

title: raisin apple cake
directions: Stir together flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a large bowl, beat together eggs, honey, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir the dry ingredients into the egg mixture.
Stir in the chopped apples and the raisins.
Put in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: south carolina macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain well.
Add grated cheese and all other ingredients except crackers.
Mix well.
Place in a greased casserole.
Put cracker crumbs on top.
Cook at 350° for about 45 minutes.
(Always a hit!)

title: karen's rolls or bread
directions: Dissolve yeast
in
warm
water;
let
it sit for a few minutes.
Add flour
in
2 parts (for whole wheat bread, add 2 cups whole
wheat
flour and 4 cups white).
Knead dough, then put in oiled
bowl.
Let
rise for 1 hour.
Make into rolls or bread and let
rise
for
1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes for rolls and 30 minutes for bread.

title: vegetable sushi
directions: Cut carrots, zucchini and avocado into slivers.
Cook rice. Warm sushi sheets to make more flexible.
Spread rice over sheets 1 inch from one and and 2 inches from other end.
Wet the ends. Lay slivers of carrots, zucchini and avocado and roll tight.
Roll back and forth to seal ends.
Cut rolls into 1-inch pieces.
Be careful in cutting.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Drain Veg-All.
Pour in 1/2 cup of milk and soup.
Heat in a boiler until it is completely warm.
Cook chicken until done. Pull off the bone and place in bottom of one pie shell.
Pour Veg-All mixture over the chicken.
Place the other pie shell on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mrs. salvo's cheese biscuits
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Measure oil in measuring cup, add milk to cup; without stirring milk and oil together.
Pour into flour and stir with fork until dough cleans bowl.
Add cheese.
Roll into balls. Flatten with fork or bake at 425°.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix sugar with cornstarch and salt.
Add cherries and cook in saucepan until mixture comes to boil; add butter.
Line pie pan with pastry.
Add cherry mixture and cover with strips of pastry. Bake in a moderate oven about 350° until golden brown.

title: play dough
directions: *Alum is found in the spice section of the store.

title: venison patties with gravy
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except soup.
Make into thick patties.
Arrange in skillet and cook until done.
In mixing bowl, add soup and 1 can water and whip together.
Pour over patties in skillet and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Gravy will turn light brown in color.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add crushed vanilla wafers and milk alternately.
Fold in coconut and pecans. Bake in tube pan at 275° for 2 hours.

title: oven pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in a skillet in oven.
Mix flour, milk and eggs.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Use topping of choice.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil spaghetti according to directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Add all ingredients.
Toss and chill.

title: frosted kiwi meringue
directions: Line the bottom of a 9-inch layer pan with brown paper.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until frothy and add vanilla. Beat in sugar a little at a time.
Continue beating until it becomes stiff. Spread in pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 225°.
Turn off oven and leave inside for 1 more hour to cool slowly.
Finish cooling at room temperature. Carefully invert pan and place on a plate. Meringue will be crumbly on bottom and around edges.
Beat whipping cream and 2 tablespoons sugar in a bowl until stiff. Frost meringue gently, starting with sides.
Sprinkle with almonds and arrange kiwi slices on top.
Serve.

title: mama's cracker pie
directions: Combine cream, egg yolks, milk, sugar, and vanilla in a pot. Heat to a full boil, stirring continually. When it comes to a full rolling boil, remove from heat and pour over crackers that have been placed in a pan. Add topping.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash lettuce and spinach; dry well. Slice onions and mushrooms.
In a large bowl, layer as follows:
lettuce, spinach, mushrooms, onions and chopped eggs.
Do not mix.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: cheese cake
directions: Roll crackers fine; mix with oleo and sugar.
Place in a 9-inch pie plate.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix flour, cocoa and sugar.
Add milk, a little at a time, to make a paste, then add the rest.
When it gets thick, add butter and vanilla.
Stir well and serve over biscuits or toast.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow all cheeses to soften at room temperature for about 1 hour.
Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Make a ball and roll in chopped pecans and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix margarine and peanut butter. Add sugar. Mix well.
Will be very thick. Dip in melted almond bark.
(Makes two 18 ounce jars full.)
Set on waxed paper until hard or put in refrigerator to speed up process.

title: tapioca mandarin orange dessert
directions: Dissolve jello and tapioca in boiling water.
Stir well. Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, whip well.
Add Cool Whip and blend.
Fold in oranges.

title: crab-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F. remove mushroom stems, mince, and combine with crab, bread crumbs, chives, lemon juice, and eggs. Stuff mushroom caps with mixture; place on lightly oiled baking sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until stuffing is golden. Serve immediately or refrigerate and reheat in microwave later to serve.

title: squash cucumber pickles
directions: Slice and combine cucumbers, onions and squash.
Add salt. Let stand for 3 hours then drain.
Combine seasonings and vinegar. Bring to a boil.
Add cucumber squash and onions.
Heat to simmering.
Point and pack in hot sterilized jars.
Seal immediately (do not boil pickles, as this will cause them to become soft).

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie pan 2/3 full of apples.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Mix milk and cream together; freeze.
Easy and delicious!

title: broccoli salad
directions: Place broccoli, onion and bacon in a bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Pour over broccoli, onion and bacon. Let set 3 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: black - bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill.
Serve with Tostitos chips.

title: chicken tortellini soup
directions: In large saucepot, combine water, chicken broth, soup, chicken, onions, carrots, garlic, basil and oregano.
Bring to a boil; add tortellini.
Simmer, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes. Add broccoli.
Simmer an additional 5 to 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Serve with cheese.
Makes 30 (1 1/2 cup servings).

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Add milk to salad oil and stir into flour.
Put mixture in 9-inch pie plate and shape to form crust.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually. Beat until light. Separate egg whites from yolks. Add yolks, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition (see below for use of egg whites). Beat in honey.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk. Beat only until smooth. Stir in nuts and fruits.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except crackers and butter. Combine crushed crackers and butter; put on top of green bean mixture in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: easy brisket roast
directions: Cover roast with sauce and bake in slow oven at 150° for 24 hours.
Easy for a party.

title: bread pudding
directions: Sauce:
To 3 cups milk, add sugar and nutmeg and warm. Thicken with cornstarch.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Fry bacon in wok.
Remove.
Crumble and set aside.
Drop eggs into bacon fat and fry.
Remove and set aside.
Add chicken and saute until tender.
Remove.
Add small amount of vegetable oil, if needed.
Add pepper and onion; saute until tender.
Return bacon, eggs and chicken to wok.
Add rice and stir to mix.
Add soy sauce to your taste.
Leave in wok and serve.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: In oven, toast oats and coconut until golden brown.
Thoroughly cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well. Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture and blend well.
Stir in oats and coconut.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cooking sheet.
Flatten with tumbler dipped in sugar. Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned. Makes 4 dozen.

title: strawberry shortcake dessert
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Add strawberries.
Set bowl aside. In separate bowl, add Dream Whip.
Use directions on package. Fold into jello mixture.
Break angel food cake into pieces and drop into the jello/Cool Whip mixture.
Fold in.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate until set up.
Can be cut into squares to serve.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add eggs, vanilla, cinnamon, coconut, orange slices and pecans.
Mix in flour with soda mixture.
Cook on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 15 minutes. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
I try to flour my chopped orange slices the night before,
makes them easier to handle.
Use the flour that has already been measured.

title: ghirardelli brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using a spoon, stir eggs with sugar and vanilla; add butter.
Mix Ghirardelli ground chocolate with flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture; add nuts.
Spread into greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: indian rice
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and cook until golden. Add rice and cook, stirring continuously, until light brown.
Add broth, raisins and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Stir and cover. Reduce heat; simmer 14 minutes.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Grease a large cookie sheet well.
Dust with flour; shake off excess and set aside.
In a small bowl beat egg whites until foamy; add salt and beat until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar 1 tablespoon at a time and beat until very stiff.
Fold in extracts and coconut until well blended.
Place rounded teaspoonfuls 1 inch apart on a cookie sheet.
With fingers dipped in cold water, smooth mounds.
Top each with a cherry half.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 12-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk as directed on package.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Put half of the pudding on graham crackers. Top with another layer of crackers and then the rest of the pudding.
Let stand for awhile in refrigerator and then top with cherry pie filling. Cool overnight.

title: ribs?
directions: Cook ribs at 350° on cookie sheet until done. Coat with sauce. Broil briefly.

title: chicken stuff
directions: Brown chicken in skillet.
Put in a baking dish.
Put the cheese over the chicken.
Put the chicken soup on the cheese, then the dressing.
Add onion, celery and apple to stuffing, if desired. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rannie mae chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda, and salt.
Combine remaining ingredients. Beat and add dry ingredients.
Stir in 1 pkg. chocolate chips.
Bake in 350 degree oven until lightly browned. Do not overbake.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with raw vegetables.

title: brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring water to boil.
Mix together brownie mix, water, oil and 1 egg in large bowl.
Pour into greased and floured 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Mix ingredients. Lay shrimp on 9 x 13 pan. Pour mixture over shrimp. Broil shrimp on each side until pink, around a minute each side.

title: bacon cheese potatoes
directions: Place potato slices on large pieces of heavy foil.
Cover with onion, celery and green pepper.
Season with salt, pepper and butter.
Sprinkle with bacon and cover with cheese.
Seal tightly. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Also can be prepared on grill.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer the broccoli in an 8 x 11-inch casserole pan.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over broccoli.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in preheated oven.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions; drain. Combine with cheese, celery, onion, mayonnaise and pepper.
Turn mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine crackers and margarine. Sprinkle over vegetable mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chicken 'n rice casserole
directions: Stir together onion soup mix, rice, cream of chicken soup and water; put in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Put chicken on top; cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and continue baking until done.
Serves 6.

title: fruit cake recipe
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs and orange juice.
Then add flour, nutmeg, and cinnamon.
Then add fruit and nuts.
Bake in tube pan approximately 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees.

title: chocolate eclair cake(make night before)
directions: You will need a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add soups, enchilada sauce and milk.
Cook to blend.
Crush chips in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour meat mixture over chips.
Place grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with flour tortillas.

title: avocado dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keep in closed jars.
When ready to serve, add 2 teaspoons of the mix to a cup of hot water.

title: creamy waldorf salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients, except lettuce, in medium bowl.
Add cream cheese mixture and toss gently.
Cover and chill. Serve in lettuce lined bowl.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot dog appetizers
directions: Cut hot dogs in small pieces.
Mix all together in saucepan and simmer for 30 minutes on low.
The girls love these!

title: glorified burritos
directions: Heat burritos and chili separately as stated on wrappers. Place a burrito on plate, top with chili, lettuce, tomatoes, onions and cheese.
Serve with Spanish rice and beans.
Serves 4.

title: icebox potato rolls
directions: Measure the warm (not hot) water into mixing bowl.
Add yeast and stir to dissolve.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, eggs, flour and mashed potatoes, mixing well.
Turn mixture onto floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, greasing top of dough.
Cover with damp cloth to store in refrigerator for use as needed.

title: chocolate torte
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and 1/2 cup nuts.
Press in bottom of 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake approximately 15 minutes or until golden brown in 300° oven.
Cool completely.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Grind together cranberries, apples, orange and orange peeling. Add sugar.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: party appetizers
directions: Mix raw chuck with seasonings.
Spread on thin party rye bread.
Place in oven at 450° until brown.
Serve hot.

title: swiss fondue
directions: Cube the bread.
Combine all ingredients until cheese melts. Spear bread with forks and dip.
Makes 2 cups.

title: "summer" cheese bake
directions: Cook the macaroni as label directs and drain. Combine with the soup, milk and beans.
Pour into a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Alternate overlapping slices of cheese (your choice) and tomatoes (3 or 4) on top.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: lumpia shanghai
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.

title: soda cracker candy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet with foil.
Place 1 layer of soda crackers on top of foil.
Stirring constantly, bring two sticks of margarine to a boil and continue stirring for 3 minutes.
Pour the margarine over the crackers and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Melt 3/4 pound chocolate and spread it on top of the margarine and crackers.
Cool in refrigerator and cut or break into pieces.

title: quick buttermilk rolls
directions: Sift flour, salt, sugar and soda in mixing bowl.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add yeast, buttermilk and shortening to flour.
Beat until well mixed.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Turn onto floured board and knead into rolls.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: cherry winks
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Mix until well combined.
Stir in nuts, dates and chopped cherries.

title: shrimp fondue casserole
directions: Clean and devein shrimp.
Remove crusts from bread.
Spread bread generously with butter and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Arrange alternate layers of bread, shrimp and cheese in 8-inch casserole. Combine slightly beaten eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over contents in casserole.
Set casserole in hot water.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar and canned milk to a boil and boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Take off burner.
Add marshmallow whip, peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into square pan.
Cool.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Combine with remaining ingredients; mix well. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine and mix until coated.
Chill overnight.
Add cucumbers and tomatoes a few hours before serving.
Toss well.

title: chopped liver
directions: Preheat broiler.
Broil livers for 1 minute on each side. Chop onion coarsely.
Add liver and chop until fairly smooth.
Add eggs and chop them coarsely.
Mix in butter and season to taste. Serve immediately or store in refrigerator.
Serve with thin slices of buttered toast.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute ground beef in skillet until crumbly.
Combine with remaining ingredients in baking dish; mix well.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.
Then bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dirt cake(very low-fat.  no bake)
directions: You will need a new 8-inch plastic flowerpot and new hand-size garden spade (to use as spoon for serving).

title: yeast waffles
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm milk in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill overnight.
Bake in hot waffle iron until brown.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: Stir soups and milk in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add green onions, celery and garlic.
Season with Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Add mushrooms and shrimp; simmer 20 minutes or until shrimp are done.
Add Madeira.
Season with salt, pepper and parsley.
Crab meat may be used instead of shrimp.
Serves 8.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a large pot, melt butter, sugar, corn syrup and salt. Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Add baking soda and vanilla. Stir quickly.
Pour over popcorn, coating well. Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix well until medium thick.
Make as much as needed.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix together in order.
Bake in a greased pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
While hot, spread 1 jar Marshmallow Creme.
Then frost with icing.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Bring sauerkraut to a boil, then drain.
Put in casserole; add remainder of ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: chocolate cool whip cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 9-inch cake pans.
After cake is baked, split layers in half.
Ice bottom of cake and put Cool Whip on top of icing.
Keep layering, then ice cake on top and sides.

title: mushroom cheeseburger pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Grease 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch pan. Unroll dough and place in greased pan. Starting at center, press out with hands. Bake at 425° for 5 to 8 minutes or until golden brown. Brown ground beef in medium skillet; drain. Stir in pizza sauce and mushrooms; spoon hamburger mixture over partially baked crust. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until deep golden brown.

title: ham & broccoli quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Layer ham, cheese & broccoli in crust. In medium bowl combine remaining ingredients and pour over ham/broccoli. Bake 35 to 45 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: salad dressing
directions: Blend well in blender.
Let set in refrigerator (covered) until ready to serve.
Makes 2 cups.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix the ingredients in a bowl. Shape into loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: witches cream
directions: Bake apples and put through a sieve.
Mix the crushed pineapple with sugar and stir into apple puree.
Add rum and egg white.
Stir until smooth.

title: beef and cheese ball
directions: Put beef in blender and chop fine.
Mix cream cheese, onion , Accent and sauce together.
Use hands to mix for best results. Blend 1/2 cup remaining beef until well coated.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; press into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes.
Let cool. Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy; add 1/3 cup sugar, mixing until well blended.
Fold in whipped topping and spread over crust.
Combine gelatin and boiling water in a bowl, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Add cold water and chill until partially set.
Stir in strawberries; pour over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate until firm.
(Can be made low-fat and low-sugar.)

title: karen's fruit punch
directions: Combine jello with 1 cup hot water and 1 cup cold water to dissolve.
Add sugar, pineapple juice and the juice of 6 lemons. Pour into a 1 gallon jug and fill remainder of jug with water. Add ginger ale after mixing in punch bowl.
Serves 50.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients with oil until blended.
Drop batter by heaping tablespoon into hot oil.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes until brown turning once.
Drain; serve with syrup or powdered sugar.
Makes 6 servings.
Can substitute corn with apples, chopped.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream together well the butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add salt; beat until well blended.
Add soda to flour and sift together.
Add sour cream and flour alternately.
Add vanilla and beat all together thoroughly.
Place in refrigerator for 3 hours or overnight.
Drop by teaspoon on buttered sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: polichinken
directions: Beat the eggs well and add the milk, flour and a pinch of salt.
Spray pan with PAM, pour 1/4 cup of batter into a sma ll hot frying pan.
Tilt the pan until it coats the bottom and forms a thin omelette with a ruffled edge.
Flip onto a plate.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef with onion soup mix in pan.
Drain.
Place in bowl. Add beans, tomatoes (quartered), lettuce and cheese.
Add taco chips and dressing just before serving.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Let cool.
Add pineapple. Chill until slightly thickened.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Can be spooned from bowl or poured into 8 x 8-inch dish.

title: gnocchi
directions: Mix all together.
Roll out like snakes.
Cut into pieces. Place on tray; either cook or freeze.
Holds 4 months uncooked.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and milk with beaten egg yolks.
Cook until thick and add coconut and vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell. Cover with beaten egg whites.
Place in oven until lightly browned. Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Allow to cool a bit, then add 1 large Cool Whip, the mini marshmallows and mandarin oranges.
Stir well.
Chill until set.

title: chocolate oatmeal-no bake cookies
directions: Mix together in saucepan milk, sugar, cocoa and butter; bring to boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: creamsicle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Cool and slice layers in half. Blend coconut, sour cream and coconut together. Set 1 cup aside. Spread evenly between layers.
Blend 1 cup filling and 1 carton Cool Whip.
Spread over cake and refrigerate 24 hours before cutting.

title: hero-toasted cod with lemon rosemary
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Remove skillet from heat and add bread crumbs, walnuts, peel and juice of 1 lemon, half of the rosemary and half of the parsley.
Press the bread crumb mixture over the top of the filets.
Place the filets in a shallow, foil-lined roasting pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Mix garlic, the remaining lemon peel and juice, rosemary, parsley and chili in a bowl.
Beat walnut oil and mix to combine well.
Drizzle this dressing over and as soon as they are cooked.
Transfer to serving plates and serve immediately.
Serve 4.

title: meat ball hot dish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape in balls and cook in skillet until meat is done.
Remove meat; add 2 tablespoons flour and 2 cups milk.
Cook and stir.
Pour over meatballs and serve.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms; remove stems.
Chop stems; set aside. In a 4-cup glass measure, combine bacon, green pepper and onion. Cover with paper towels and cook on High for 4 minutes, stirring once.
Drain off fat.
Add salt, cream cheese, Worcestershire and mushroom stems.
Mix well.
Fill mushrooms with bacon mixture. In a 2-cup glass measure, mix butter, bread crumbs and parsley. Cook on High 1 minute.
Press bread crumbs into top of bacon mixture.
Place half the mushrooms in a 9-inch microproof baking dish, stuffing side up.
Cook on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Repeat with remaining mushrooms.

title: curried cheese log
directions: Combine cheeses and beat until well blended and fluffy.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill until firm enough to handle.
In a small saucepan, melt butter; stir in curry powder and saute, stirring 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts; cool.
Shape cheese mixture into a 8-inch long roll.
Roll in curried nut mixture to coat well and sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Wrap tightly in waxed paper and chill.

title: chocolate dream cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar into mixing bowl; blend well.
Bring margarine, shortening, water and cocoa to rapid boil in saucepan; pour over flour and sugar mixture and mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients and add all at once to batter.
Mix well.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom only of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing well; set aside. Beat orange juice, eggs, oil and orange peel until mixed thoroughly.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened. Stir in cranberries and nuts.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix soda in sour cream and allow to dissolve.
Cream butter and sugar together and add eggs (one at a time).
Add flour, salt and sour cream alternately.
Then add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into well greased and floured Bundt pan or steeple pan.
Set oven at 300° and place cake in cold oven.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not overbake.
While hot, put on cake plate with top on it and it will be real moist.
(If moisture accumulates on cover, wipe dry.)

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Boil chicken; set aside after removing from bone.
Take flour tortillas and place chicken and cheese on top.
Cover with additional tortilla.
Place on griddle until lightly brown and cheese melts.
Remove, top with salad, sour cream and guacamole. Serve hot.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix and bake until thickened and light brown at 350°.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Put cabbage head in boiling water.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients, except tomato juice and stuff leaves with mixture and roll up.
Put in kettle with tomato juice.
Simmer for 4 or 5 hours.
Close cabbage leaves with toothpicks.

title: cocktail sandwich spread
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Mix mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Refrigerate in jar until ready to use.
Slice small French bread or poor boy rolls (2 1/2 to 3-inch size).
Spread cocktail mix on bread slices and place on cookie sheet under broiler for a few minutes until cheese melts and begins to brown.
Serve warm.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning. Put this mixture in the bottom of a pie pan.
Keep cold.
Layer chopped lettuce, onions, peppers and tomatoes.
Pour 8-ounce jar taco sauce over top.
Put shredded Cheddar cheese on last.
Serve with taco chips as a dip.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Add taco seasoning. Stir in remaining ingredients and place in baking dish.
Prepare cornbread as directed on box.
Pour over the ground beef mixture. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: elbow macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly; add seasonings.
Cook until sauce is thickened.
Add 1 cup grated sharp Cheddar cheese and stir until melted.
Cook macaroni
in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain.
Add to cheese sauce; mix well.
Turn mixture into 8-inch square baking dish or pan.
Sprinkle top with 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for about 15 minutes. Remove from oven.
Place under broiler until cheese is bubbly and lightly browned.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dill bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Cover.
Let double in size (1 to 1 1/2 hours) in warm kitchen.
Stir down.
Pour into greased pan.
Let rise 40 to 75 minutes until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
While hot, brush with butter.

title: blueberry cream pie *
directions: Bake pie shells and cool.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed and add nuts; refrigerate.
Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add the two mixtures together.
Cut up bananas and place in cooled pie shells. Pour mixture over bananas and top with pie filling.
(Cherry pie filling may be used instead of blueberry.)
Refrigerate several hours.
This makes two pies.

title: hot pepper corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray cake pan with nonstick shortening spray.
Mix all ingredients until moist.
Batter will be lumpy. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until browns on top.

title: cracker snacks
directions: Mix together Ritz or Club crackers, brown sugar, walnuts and butter.
Spread on crackers.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: mission baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 475° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 15 minutes longer (8 to 12).

title: irish bread
directions: *These items should be at room temperature.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix according to package. Pour into a wax paper-lined greased pan, 9 x 13-inch (deep).
Mix remaining ingredients until blended.
Pour into center of cake batter.
Do not mix in.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.

title: whole egg custard(reduced calories)
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add other ingredients; beat after each addition.
Spray custard cups with Pam.
Pour in mixture.
Place cups in pan of water.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: almond raspberry brie
directions: Slice Brie in half horizontally.
Place bottom half of Brie on a microwave-safe serving plate.
Combine jam and Chambord, if desired; spread on cheese, leaving
a 1-inch margin around edge and top with remaining cheese half.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and almonds and drizzle with honey.
Microwave at High 1 minute or just until soft.
Serve immediately with wafer cookies, melba rounds or gingersnaps.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, flour and sugar.
Mix in egg yolks.
Slowly add milk, vanilla and margarine.
Cook over double boiler until creamy and thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: mini meat loaves
directions: Set rack in cookwell.
Preheat 6-quart roaster oven to 350°. Combine beef, bread crumbs, 2 tablespoons of cheese and milk granules in medium mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except for barbecue sauce; stir until well mixed.
Form into 4 loaves. Place loaves on rack.
Brush barbecue sauce evenly over meat. Sprinkle on remaining Parmesan cheese.
Cover.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes (150° to 160° on meat thermometer).

title: bacon-asparagus quiche
directions: Drain and crumble the bacon; set aside.
Brush mustard evenly over bottom and sides of pastry shell.
Bake shell at 375° for 15 minutes or until firm, but not completely browned.
Sprinkle baked crust with the bacon and arrange cooked, drained asparagus over. Sprinkle with half the Swiss cheese.
Mix eggs, cream, salt, pepper, tarragon and savory.
Pour over mixture in the shell.
Top with remaining Swiss cheese.
Return to oven and bake about 25 to 35 minutes or until quiche is set in the center (a butter knife inserted in the center comes out clean).

title: maple fudge
directions: Pour hot mixture over last 4 ingredients and mix until all is dissolved.
Pour into tinfoil lined pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Put walnut halves on top of each square.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: zesty fried chicken
directions: Combine in mixing bowl the corn meal, paprika, salt, garlic powder, pepper and cumin.
Rinse chicken.
Coat evenly with corn meal mixture.
Spray a cold large skillet with nonstick spray. Cook until done.

title: overnight rolls
directions: Mix water, sugar, butter or margarine and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix 1/2 teaspoon sugar, 2 tablespoons warm water and yeast; stir to dissolve, then add to first mixture.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir in 2 cups of the flour; beat well about 3 minutes. Add remaining 2 cups flour and beat.
Refrigerate until very cold. Roll for rolls.
Brush with melted butter; sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and cut.
Put into greased pan.
Let set on cupboard overnight.

title: campbell's easy chicken pot pie
directions: *Or use Campbell's| cream of chicken with herbs soup.

title: autumn supreme apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar; set aside.
Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Add apples and other ingredients to flour mixture and mix well.
(I use my hand.)
Bake in greased and floured tube pan or sheet pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together and spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: speed snack(dream shake)
directions: Whirl ingredients in blender.
This creamy low-fat shake is a tasty pick-me-up.

title: blender hollandaise
directions: Heat to bubbling
the stick of butter.	Place all other ingredients in blender, cover and turn on.	Take off cover and pour butter into
other
ingredients in a steady stream.
Turn off blender and serve.

title: fantastic fudge
directions: Grease an 8-inch pan.
Cut marshmallows into small bits. Measure out 1 1/2 cups and set aside.
Put milk, sugar and butter in saucepan over low heat.
Heat to boiling and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, nuts, chocolate and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows and chocolate are melted (about 1 minute).
Pour into pan.
Allow to cool and then cut into squares.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Butter casserole.
Heat soup, cheese and butter.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour into casserole.
Pour soup mixture slowly into casserole and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Pour tomato juice in shallow baking dish.
Roll chicken in juice.
Leave chicken with skin side up and sprinkle with spices above.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Turn and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: real brunswick stew
directions: Prepare and mix all ingredients.
Simmer slowly, stirring often to keep from sticking.
Stock from chicken and pork may be used to make stew desired thickness.
Cooking time is 1 hour.

title: ruth's chicken
directions: Clean chicken parts.
Remove all fat and skin.
Add lemon juice to water.
Pat chicken parts dry (paper towel).

Season chicken with salt, black pepper, onion powder and garlic powder. On top of stove, saute garlic, onions, green and red peppers and vegetable flakes in 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil (do not brown). Remove from skillet.
Add 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil.
Add chicken parts until brown.
Spoon sauteed seasonings over chicken parts; add tomato sauce, sugar and cayenne red pepper.
Add water and cook for 15 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Add mushrooms and continue to cook until chicken is done.
Remove bay leaves. Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Stew chicken with salt, pepper and bay leaf.
After cooking, bone and cut chicken into bite size pieces.
In a large saucepan, cook bell pepper and onion in margarine or butter until tender. Stir in soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a tube pan.

title: sparkling punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan and simmer 5 minutes. Set aside for several hours.
Strain syrup and discard spices.
At serving time combine all but 7-Up in a large punch bowl.
Then slowly pour in 7-Up.
Add ice and garnish with slices of lemon and lime.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Thoroughly combine crushed fruit and yogurt in a bowl.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending well.
Spoon into a crust and freeze about 4 hours.
Remove from freezer and place in refrigerator for 30 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat the yolks into the brown sugar, then beat in the butter.
Beat egg whites until stiff, and fold in lightly. Add raisins and beat a few minutes longer.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate candy bar dessert
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, mix crumbs, 1/4 cup of sugar and butter. Press firmly onto bottom of pan. Refrigerate 10 minutes. In medium bowl, beat cream cheese and remaining 1/4 cup sugar with wire whisk until smooth. Gently stir in half of whipped topping. Spread mixture evenly over crust. Sprinkle chopped candy bars over cream cheese layer. Pour milk into large bowl. Add pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk 1 minute. Pour over chopped candy bar layer. Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened. Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding layer. Refrigerate 2 hours or until set. Sprinkle with additional chopped candy bars, if desired. Cut into squares and serve. Store leftover dessert in the refrigerator.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: jello cake
directions: Prepare each package of jello as per package instructions. Chill until almost set.
Meanwhile, slice angel food cake into thin slices.
When jello is ready, spoon some of each flavor alternately into a 9 x 13-inch pan, forming a thin layer on the bottom.
Next, place a layer of angel food cake over the jello.
Spread some of each kind of fruit over the cake.
Repeat layers, ending with a jello layer.
Chill until firm.
Serve with Cool Whip if desired.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Boil V-8 juice and chopped onion; simmer for 3 minutes.
Put Jell-O in a bowl and add the juice and mix.
Add vinegar, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and olives.
Pour into 1-quart mold or 6 individual molds.

title: southern collard greens
directions: Thoroughly wash and cut collards.
Put water and ham hock in large pot with a tight fitting lid.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat to very low and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add collards and pepper flakes.
Simmer, covered, for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add salad oil; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. Check seasoning.
Add more to taste.
The long cooking time is essential for the flavor.
Serve with corn bread.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Heat oil in a large pot. Add garlic, onion, celery and parsley. Cook until soft.
Add tomato paste and next 8 ingredients.
Mix well. Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 1 hour. Add beans and macaroni. Cook 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Mix diced chicken, mushroom soup, chicken broth, picante sauce or salsa and chopped onion together.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together cream of chicken soup and broth.
Pour in thin film in bottom of dish.
Put little of mixture in tortilla and roll.
Place in dish.
Pour rest of cream of chicken soup mixture over and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach tea
directions: Add 7-Up just before serving.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Place noodles in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next 5 ingredients and pour over noodles.
Add Mozzarella cheese on top of sauce.
Mix next 3 ingredients and pour over Mozzarella cheese.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: apple grape salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Mix lightly, cover and refrigerate.

title: mexican dip(cold tray)
directions: Use equal amounts of cream cheese and sour cream (I used 16 ounces of each).
Mix thoroughly and add enough hot taco sauce to a light pink coloring.
Form and flatten on a large round tray. On top layer the following vegetables: tomatoes, green peppers, scallions, avocado and olives.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and add additional taco sauce on top.
Serve with Doritos chips.

title: bread sticks
directions: Roll out the dough and put in a jelly roll pan. Melt oleo; spread on dough. Mix together the spices and sprinkle over dough. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Put in the refrigerator until the oleo is set. Cut into serving pieces. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Can make early in the day and refrigerate until baking time. Can freeze baked bread sticks, warm in microwave.

title: drunk hot dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients except hot dogs in large pan; cook for 20 minutes.
Add hot dogs to sauce; cook until liquid has boiled down and is slightly thick.
Can be put in the crock-pot on low for about 6 hours.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into cubes.
Cook in boiling salt water. Drain well.
Mash eggplant down with a fork.
Brown ground beef in butter with spices, onion and green pepper.
Stir in eggplant and cooked rice.
Spoon into lightly greased Pyrex casserole. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and grated Romano cheese.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: oven-made caramel corn
directions: Put corn in 250° oven to keep warm.
