Combine all ingredients, except baking soda.
Place over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Boil to firm ball stage (248°).
Remove from heat. Stir in baking soda.
(It will foam.)
Pour over corn and mix well.
Place in shallow pans.
Return to oven for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and place in airtight containers.

title: banana bread (cake-like)
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then mashed bananas and sour cream or buttermilk.
Sift baking soda and flour and add. (Batter looks curdled.)
Use a 9 x 5 x 2-inch greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Boil and drain macaroni. In a casserole dish, add macaroni, evaporated milk, plus enough water to make liquid come to the top of the macaroni. Cut butter into little slices. Place around dish. Add eggs. Place slices of cheese all around dish evenly so cheese will be in all areas. Add salt and pepper to taste. Bake, covered, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: red rice
directions: Fry bacon; remove and place on paper towel.
Brown onions and bell peppers in drippings.
Add tomatoes, sauce, Tabasco and crumbled bacon.
Pour in greased casserole; sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until rice is dry enough to separate.

title: blueberry oven pancake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Beat all ingredients, except blueberries, with wire whisk or hand beater until well blended.
Fold in blueberries.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes or until top is light golden brown.
Cut into 12 pieces.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ragu-by-the-sea
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in tuna and saute briefly.
Add spaghetti sauce and parsley.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over macaroni.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: charm cake
directions: Cream well together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Whip after each egg.
Add vanilla wafer crumbs and milk to mixture.
Fold in coconut and pecans.
Grease and flour a tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Must be cooled completely before removing from pan.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Mix all ingredients and put in casserole.
Bake 2 hours at 300°..
Turn oven off and let stand 1 hour.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix together.
Add small amount water if dough seems stiff. Pack firmly in pastry tube.
Squeeze in long strands.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cut into sticks immediately on removal from the oven.
Let cool slightly before removing from the pan.

title: strawberry-fig jam
directions: Dissolve jello into water.
Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Pack in jars.

title: lazy crazy chocolate cake
directions: Add ingredients in order given, except for vanilla.
Beat for 2 minutes, then add vanilla.
Beat 1 more minute.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch or 9-inch round pan.

title: rice dish
directions: Brown meat and onion together with salt and pepper and add soup, tomatoes and spices.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers, onions and green pepper with cold water.
Add salt.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, drain water off.
Rinse well.
Mix sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Mix into cucumbers. Then freeze.

title: brisket pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle beef with salt and pepper. Place in a large skillet.
Brown meat on fat side over high heat. While meat is browning, pare carrots and potatoes. Cut in chunks. Slice onions.
Remove meat and place in large roasting pan.
Add onions to skillet.
Saute until golden brown.
Spoon onions over meat.
Surround meat with vegetables.
Add 1 cup water.
Roast covered 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until meat is done.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise in mixer bowl. Beat until smooth. Add next 7 ingredients, blending well. Refrigerate until easily shaped. Roll into ball. Roll in pecans or sesame seed. Refrigerate until firm.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain
kidney
beans.
Mix
all ingredients thoroughly. Refrigerate a few hours before serving to improve flavor.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add nutmeg.
Add eggs and beat until ingredients are mixed.
Add vanilla and milk.
Pour into a pie crust that has been rinsed with ice water.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 25 minutes (or until pie is set).

title: french bean casserole
directions: Place beans in greased casserole.
Cover with soup and onions on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: cherry delight
directions: Take crumbs and 1/2 cup sugar and butter and mix together. Put in a 13 x 9 pan. Beat cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Pour over graham cracker crust and bake until set, 10 to 15 minutes. Put the cherries on top with whip cream.

title: charolais beef stew
directions: Roll meat in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in canola oil. Place meat in Dutch oven; pour the other ingredients over it. Simmer, covered, about 4 hours.
Add more water, if needed.
Cook 6 potatoes and 6 carrots (quartered) and 1 stalk celery separately, until tender; add to meat mixture the last 15 minutes of cooking time.

title: spicy bacon-banana wraps
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Combine broccoli, corn, egg, salt and pepper in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Blend stuffing and butter or margarine.
Sprinkle on top of broccoli-corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs very slightly.
Add all other ingredients and blend. Fold into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in oven for 45 to 60 minutes at 300°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Brown onion, bell pepper and celery.
Add tomatoes, mushroom soup and celery soup.
Mix all ingredients, including chicken, together in a large oiled baking dish.
Cook at 300° for about 30 minutes.
When it is hot all the way through, remove from oven and sprinkle 1 pound of grated cheese on top, followed with layer of chopped pimentos and sliced green olives.

title: crab cheese canapes
directions: Mix all together and spread on muffins.
Cut into fourths and freeze on cookie sheet.
After they are frozen, you can stack these.
Cook while frozen.
Broil about 5 minutes or until brown. Add paprika to top, if desired.

title: aunt jan's chili sauce
directions: Remove skin from ham.
Add glaze 45 minutes before it is finished cooking.

title: rice casserole(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add rice, cottage cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper, Cheddar cheese and chillies.
Pour into casserole pan and bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sour cream fudge cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Combine shortening and sour cream and beat for 2 minutes.
Add chocolate, eggs, vanilla, hot water and dry ingredients.
Turn into well-greased and floured pans. Makes 2 (8-inch) pans baking for 35 minutes, 2 (9-inch) pans baking for 25 to 30 minutes or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350°.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook meat until browned; drain.
Add beans, tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Heat to boiling.
Place chips in an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with meat mixture.
Spread sour cream on top of meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until bubbly.
Serve with lettuce and taco sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Slice tomatoes and soak in salt and water overnight.
In the morning, rinse and drain.
Slice onions and add to the tomatoes. Boil vinegar, sugar and spice for 15 minutes; add to tomatoes and onions.
Boil for 15 minutes more.
Pack in hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Yields 10 pints.

title: nippy dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend until well mixed (high speed).
Empty into serving dish; cover and chill at least one hour.
Serve with crisp raw vegetables.
Makes two cups.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In greased baking dish, mix rice, soups and milk. Add uncooked chicken.
Melt together butter and sugar; stir in.
Season with garlic powder, salt and pepper. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Enjoy!
Great dish for a potluck dinner.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Combine applesauce and gelatin in small pan and let sit for 5 minutes.
Heat until simmering.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir and turn out onto plastic wrap. Knead until smooth.
Cover with second sheet of plastic and roll 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut shapes. Make holes for hangers with straw and dry on wire rack overnight.
Makes 20.

title: paul horning stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in covered casserole; bake at 250° for 5 hours until meat is tender. Or put in slow cooker.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: In 10-inch skillet, cook ground beef over medium heat until browned, drain well.

title: texas slaw
directions: Layer chopped cabbage and onions in large bowl.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar over top.
Combine vinegar, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, mustard and celery seed; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add oil.
Bring to boil again.
Pour over cabbage and onions. Cover tightly and store in refrigerator overnight.
Stir occasionally.
Drain and stir before serving.
This will keep in refrigerator for two weeks.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and make like biscuit.

title: s'mores
directions: Arrange on paper towels or napkins 1 cookie topped with 1/2 of candy bar and 1 marshmallow and cover with another cookie. Microwave on Full power for 3/4 to 1 minute in wrapped towel or napkin.
Let stand before unwrapping.
Repeat for second cookie.

title: cinnamon apple jelly
directions: Mix apple juice and Sure-Jell in large pan and bring to a boil. Add sugar.
Cook until mixture jells, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture into jars.

title: chicken(skillet)
directions: Cut chicken as for frying.
Salt and place in skillet.
Pour Coke and catsup over chicken. Simmer until chicken is done and tender, using a lid on skillet.
Remove lid and finish cooking until Coke and catsup are a thick sauce.

title: date nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: miniature pecan pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Take 1 1/2 teaspoons of dough and press into greased mini muffin pan.
This will make 2 dozen.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine.
Remove from heat and mix in the next 3 ingredients.
Press mixture into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over peanut mixture. Refrigerate 30 minutes, then cut into 1-inch pieces.
If you refrigerate longer than 30 minutes the chocolate will be difficult to cut.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Melt margarine and sweetener together until smooth.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, vanilla and walnuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with nonsugar substitute. Cool and cut into squares.
Yields:
70 squares.
Carbohydrate 2.4 g, protein .5 g, fat .9 g, calories 25.
One square = 1/2 fat exchange.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Cook chicken in nonstick skillet until done and juices evaporate, stirring often.
Add soup and salsa and heat through.

title: cauliflower-ham bake
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets; cook in boiling, salted water until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain; set aside.

title: grandma donna's crescent rolls
directions: Measure in bowl the warm water and yeast.
Stir in 1/2 cup sugar, salt, eggs, margarine and 2 cups of flour.
Add 2 more cups flour.
Cover and let rise until double (1 1/2 hours).
Divide into 4 parts (roll like pie).
Cut into 8 pieces and spread with butter. Roll into crescents.* Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
*At this point, these may be frozen.
Let rise 5 hours and bake.

title: garden fresh tomato sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes, garlic and onions in blender.
Pour into large heavy kettle.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 4 hours or until thick.
Pour into quarts or pints.
Process in hot water bath 10 minutes for pints, 15 minutes for quarts.

title: christmas wreath
directions: Melt oleo and marshmallows.
Put in vanilla and coloring; stir. Add corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper to form a wreath.
Put red cinnamon candies for berries.

title: homemade chili
directions: Cook together beef, onion and garlic until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, vanilla pudding and whipped cream.
Layer wafers, bananas, then mix.
Repeat layers, ending with pudding.

title: little smokies in glaze sauce
directions: In crock-pot, put little smokies, jar of jelly and 4 tablespoons mustard.
Set crock-pot on high until all ingredients are melted.
Set crock-pot on low and enjoy.
Great for parties. Makes a delicious finger food.

title: warm cheese dip
directions: Mix together.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: chicken stew
directions: Combine chicken, milk and butter.
Add corn.
Pull from heat and add well beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Put back over heat and cook slowly to keep the eggs from curdling.
Pull from heat and let stand a few minutes, then add tomatoes.
Put back over heat and simmer slowly.
Add crackers to thicken.
After adding crackers, salt to taste.
Will serve approximately 12 to 15 people.

title: rice and refried beans(guatemala)
directions: Rice:
Put a little cooking oil into pan.
Cook onion until tender and beginning to brown.
Add 1 cup of rice and let it fry until its begins to change color.
Add 2 cups of water and chicken bouillon cube.
Add shredded carrot and salt to taste.
Bring to boil and cook on low until water is gone-approximately 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese.
Beat cheeses together until well mixed and smooth.
Add pecans, chili powder and garlic powder.
Mix and roll into balls.
Sprinkle with extra chili powder if desired. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar, peanut butter and shortening thoroughly.
Add eggs and mix well, then add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: bing cherry ring
directions: Drain cherries and add enough water to the juice to make 2 3/4 cups.
Bring the juice to a boil and pour
over gelatin. Stir until dissolved. Cool juice and gelatin, then add the wine. Chill in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Add cherries and nuts. Pour into ring mold.
Allow to set. Excellent with avocado halves stuffed with crab or lobster salad.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt the butter in an 8 or 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle the remaining ingredients over the butter.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package and add peanut butter. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done.
Contains 169 calories per serving.

title: tasty sticks
directions: Melt oleo and add spices.
Spread on all sides of bread which has been cut in fourths (lengthwise).
Bake on cookie sheet at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dory's pumpkin cake
directions: Mix and press in bottom of well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: walnut-cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Put crumbled Ritz crackers in a buttered pie plate.
Mix together the egg whites, walnuts, vanilla and sugar.
Pour all in the pie plate and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: peggie's beer bread
directions: Heat beer to boiling point.
Add margarine to beer until melted.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, hot roll mix, brown sugar, wheat germ, salt and eggs.
Mix well. Transfer to greased bowl and let rise, covered, in warm place for 1 1/2 hours.
Knead and shape into loaves.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Blend oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt and baking powder along with water.
Add nuts, coconut, orange slices and oatmeal. Place in 2 rolls and chill overnight.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes or until brown.

title: twinkies strawberry shortcake
directions: Cut Twinkies in half lengthwise and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with cream side up.
Pour cooked vanilla pudding over Twinkies.
Top with sliced strawberries; thaw, if frozen.
Spread with Cool Whip to cover strawberries.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Remove and discard skin from chicken, cut each breast in half.
Combine bread crumbs with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Dip each seasoned chicken breast in flour, then beaten egg, then bread crumbs.
Saute chicken in olive oil until brown on both sides (about 5 minutes each side).
Combine spaghetti sauce, garlic and oregano.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken over sauce bone side down.
Cover loosely with foil; bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove foil from baking dish. Top each chicken piece with one slice of Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan.
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes or until Mozzarella is lightly browned.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and rinse 3 times.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Best made 1 day ahead.

title: potato bread
directions: Add a little milk to the mashed potatoes, salt, pepper and flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick and cut into 8 pieces.
Cook on hot griddle, browning on both sides.
Good with bacon and eggs.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Add rest of ingredients.
Serve cold.

title: raisin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then mix rest of ingredients and add to dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour into 1-quart round casserole, sprayed with a pan coating.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°. Cool 10 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: italian corn bread
directions: Mix well and bake in an iron round bread pan.
I use a frypan or iron section pan and bake at 450° for 45 minutes (or until well browned).

title: very berry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift all the dry ingredients together except topping.
Add berries and mix until well coated.
In small bowl, beat eggs well and add melted butter and milk.
Quickly stir liquid mixture into dry mix.
Stir just until blended.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Sprinkle a teaspoon of cinnamon sugar on top of each muffin.
Bake for 20 minutes or until a toothpick tests clean.
Yields 24.

title: broccoli stir-fry with ginger and garlic
directions: Place sesame seed on baking sheet and toast in preheated oven (350°) until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Do not burn.
Set aside.

title: eggless applesauce cake
directions: Mix ingredients as listed. Batter should be thick.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Penuche frosting is especially good on this moist cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dry beans
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Add desired amount of cheese and bread crumbs.
Mix in pimientos (chopped) and seasoning to taste. Bake until cheese is melted.
Add small amount of milk if more liquid is needed.

title: mock maple syrup
directions: Dissolve sugar in water in saucepan. Add salt. Boil 1 minute. Add vanilla and mix well. Serve warm.

title: orange muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in sour cream.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to batter mixture.
Stir in rind, raisins and nuts.
Fill muffin tins (greased or paper lined) half full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When still hot, glaze muffins with mixture of sugar and orange juice.

title: zesty turkey loaf
directions: Combine ground turkey with
torn
pieces of bread.
Add eggs, onion, horseradish and
mustard.
Add
tomato
sauce and mix well. Place in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours. Serves 8.

title: lemon bars deluxe
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs well and add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour over crust.
Bake for 25 minutes longer. Sprinkle top with powdered sugar when cooled.
Makes 24 bars.

title: vegetable kishke
directions: Pulverize crackers in blender.
This yields approximately 2 1/4 cups.
Set aside.
Finely chop the vegetables in blender adding some of the margarine. Mix the cracker crumbs, vegetables, margarine and salt together in a large bowl.
Oil 3 pieces of aluminum foil (8 x 12-inch).
Form the mixture into 3 rolls about 1 1/2 x 9-inches on the foil sheets.
Roll up the sheets and fold the edges to seal.
Freeze overnight or until hard.
Peel the foil and place the frozen rolls on heavily greased baking sheets or pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut into 3/4 to 1-inch slices.

title: rice with beef consomme
directions: Melt margarine. Add rice and onion; saute. Pour in casserole dish. Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice.
Add strawberry jello.
Add sliced strawberries.
Chill until thickened.
Melt 1 cup butter; add pretzels.
Add sugar and press into oblong pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, cream cheese (softened) and Cool Whip.
Pour this mixture on top of crust, then pour gelatin mixture on top of that.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: german baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and green pepper.
Combine beans and hamburger.
Add brown sugar.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Add ketchup.
Resembles chili consistency.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hershey scotch cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chocolate bars and nuts. Batter will be very thick.
Spread evenly in greased, 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven. Place chocolate bars over hot layer.
When melted, spread with knife.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: pumpkin carrot muffins
directions: In a bowl, beat together the brown sugar, oil, egg and pumpkin puree.
Add grated carrot.
In another bowl, combine the flour, baking powder and the baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into the pumpkin mixture.
Add the chocolate chips and raisins or currants just before the batter is blended.
Do not overmix batter.
Grease muffin pans.
Spoon batter almost to the top of each cup.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool a few minutes before removing from pan.
Serve fresh.

title: chocolate glaze(good on crazy cake)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook on low.
Heat until smooth (2 to 3 minutes).
Remove.
Beat in 1 cup sifted powdered sugar. Drizzle over warm cake.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mash graham crackers.
Add raisins, pecans, condensed milk, water and cherries.
Mix all ingredients well.
Put in a greased tube or loaf pan.
Use butter or margarine.
Press mixture into pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keep refrigerated.
Yum!
Yum!

title: apple dumplings
directions: Separate rolls into triangles.
Roll triangles and cut each one in two.
Peel and cut apples in quarters.
Wrap 1/2 triangle around each apple quarter.
Arrange apples in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Boil water, sugar, cinnamon and butter for 3 minutes. Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be used as a dessert or a side dish.

title: barbecues
directions: Combine ketchup, relish and Coke in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in chipped ham.
Simmer another 10 minutes.
Put on bun and enjoy.

title: crazy chocolate cake(quick and easy)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into a prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
(Add 1 egg for a shiny top.)

title: microwave chili-o-cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese into cubes.
Combine all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole dish.
Microwave on roast for 4 to 6 minutes or until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Serve with chips.

title: diabetic veggie pita pizza
directions: Dig up agave; trim leaves and stems.

title: chess cake bars
directions: Mix and press in 9x13
greased pan.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Form into medium size balls, putting into a pan in which 1 can of tomato soup and 1 can of water has been stirred and heated.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: cocktail sausage
directions: Put mini sausages in pot. Add bottle of barbecue sauce, then add hot sauce and water.
Cook for 1 hour on low heat.
Good for parties.

title: english drop cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, coffee, shortening, raisins and enough water to cook 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In mixing bowl, cream the sugar and cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in bananas and eggs.
Add biscuit mix and pecans.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil last 15 minutes if bread browns too quickly.

title: special 10-minute stroganoff
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Drain off fat.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in soup. Simmer uncovered for 5 minutes.
Blend in sour cream and heat through.
Pour over cooked noodles.

title: butterscotch crunchies
directions: Put morsels in top of double boiler over hot water; heat until morsels are dissolved or melted.
Stir in noodles and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto tray.
The size will depend on the occasion for which they will be used.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar, salt, milk and corn syrup; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until candy thermometer reaches softball stage.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Break bread crumbs.
Add broth.
Add remaining ingredients; beat slightly.
Pour into a greased shallow pan.
Bake for about 30 minutes in hot oven.
Makes 6 large servings.
Recipe may be doubled with equally good results.

title: mandarin rangers
directions: Mix
dry ingredients in large bowl.
Blend wet ingredients and pour over dry ones.
Mix and drop by large spoonfuls. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: orange breakfast rolls(these are fabulous)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Save 1 tablespoon orange juice concentrate for icing.
Mix remaining concentrate with orange zest.
Dip biscuits in concentrate and place in square or round baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle tops with Molly McButter and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and pour icing over while hot.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in microwave.
Put all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook slowly several hours.

title: meat pie with biscuits
directions: Cook diced celery, onion, potatoes and carrots in meat stock until almost tender.
Mix the diced meat into vegetables.
Pour into 2-inch deep baking dish.
Top with baking powder biscuits. Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle the top with the grated cheese.
Return to oven at 350° for 5 minutes. Serve hot.

title: vegetable lasagne(less than 30% of calories from fat)
directions: Heat oil.
Saute onion, garlic, carrots and mushrooms until tender.
Combine vegetables with spinach, Ricotta and Mozzarella. In a separate container, combine tomato sauce with basil and oregano.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Spread small amount of tomato mixture into pan.
Alternate noodles, sauce and vegetables; mix.
Top layer should be vegetable-cheese mix.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 50 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Place ingredients in blender; blend until mixed.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and top with topping.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken breasts in wine mushroom-rice pilaf
directions: Season both sides of chicken pieces with salt and pepper.
Mix vermouth, tarragon and garlic.
Add chicken.
Marinate at room temperature 1 hour, turning occasionally.
Fold chicken pieces in half lengthwise.
Place in greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish.
Pour marinade on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve on Mushroom-Rice Pilaf.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Blend thoroughly.
Spread mixture evenly in a glass loaf dish.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.
Spread on bottom of 6 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with shredded lettuce, chopped onions, chopped tomatoes and grated cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: double chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar and pudding together.
Add oil, water and eggs.
Mix only until smooth.
Stir in sour cream.
When blended, add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased Bundt pan.
Freezes well.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, mix together milk and evaporated milk.
Scald milk mixture; then set aside.

title: custard pie
directions: Heat marshmallows and milk until marshmallows are melted. Cool.
Blend in eggs, vanilla and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Bake about 50 minutes in 450° oven.

title: german apple cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel apples, core and thinly slice.
In bowl toss apples with 5 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Set aside.

title: cocoa cheesecake pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, cocoa and 1 teaspoon vanilla in a large mixing bowl until light and fluffy. Add eggs and blend well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool for about 15 to 20 minutes. Combine sour cream, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Stir until smooth. Spread over baked filling. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Allow to cool and chill overnight.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve.

title: bacardi rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan.

title: hershey's prize chocolate cake
directions: Generously grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Blend in eggs.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Store in a tightly air sealed container.
When ready to serve, add 1 to 2 teaspoons of mix to a cup of boiling water.

title: diabetic orange salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in jars with dill top and bottom of jar.
Can add 2 cloves garlic.
Pour boiling solution over cucumbers and seal jars.
(Have jars and lids sterile and hot.)
Some recommend not using city water.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Soften margarine and blend with sugar.
Add beaten eggs, coconut and pineapple, mixing well.
Add vanilla and lemon juice (you can add more juice if you like a stronger taste).
Mix and pour into the unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place all ingredients, except tomatoes, in saucepan.
Cover and boil gently for 10 minutes.
Break up tomatoes.
Add to vegetable mixture and continue cooking until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Makes 4 servings (about 1 cup each).

title: baked zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in 3 tablespoons oil in a large skillet over moderate heat, stirring often. Cook until zucchini is almost tender. Spoon zucchini mixture into a 2-quart shallow baking dish (or 13 x 9-inch).
In the same skillet, stir together the spaghetti sauce mix, water, tomato paste and remaining 1 tablespoon oil.
Heat to boiling, stirring often. Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring several times.
Pour over zucchini mixture.
Mix Parmesan and crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of casserole and stir gently to mix. Top with Mozzarella.
Heat in a 350° oven.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican cinnamon nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the brown sugar with butter and shortening.
Sift the flour with the baking soda, salt and cinnamon and add to the creamed mixture.
Add the water and nuts and stir until well blended.
Roll the dough 2 1/2
inches in diameter.
Slice the roll into 1/8-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 7 minutes.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water following package directions.
Drain.
Combine oregano with onion, pepper and spaghetti sauce.
Alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese, spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese slices in greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix together jello, hot and cold water; let slightly jell, then add pineapple, bananas, marshmallows and apple; let jell.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed. Simmer soups and cheese until creamy. Add chicken and spaghetti. Mix well and pour into 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together sugar, peanut butter and melted margarine in large bowl.
Roll into little balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler or microwave.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture.
Put on wax paper.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In an ungreased 8-inch pan, bake for 30 minutes until apples are tender.
Top is golden brown.

title: super chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch dish except chicken and paprika.
Place chicken onto rice mixture.
Sprinkle paprika on chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugar-free cake
directions: Mix and bake at 300° about 1 hour.
This cake is good.

title: super spinach appetizer
directions: Grease oblong baking dish.
Combine ingredients in bowl.
Pour into prepared baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cut into squares.

title: harvest stewed corn and tomatoes
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Scrape to remove any liquid.
Combine all ingredients.
Bring to simmer; cover.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes until veggies are cooked.
Serve in bowls over crumbled soda crackers.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press into 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great for breakfast, topped with cooked apples or warm milk.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix all five ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: parmesan yogurt chicken
directions: Arrange
chicken pieces in a single layer in casserole. Drizzle lemon juice over chicken. Blend remaining ingredients. Stir in green onions and spread over chicken. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: apple jelly
directions: Add apple juice and sugar and stir well.
Boil over high heat above the boiling point of water or until jelly mixture sheets from a spoon.
Remove from heat.
Skim off foam quickly.
Pour jelly immediately into hot, sterilized glasses and seal with paraffin.
Makes 4 or 5 glasses.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together well and chill.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix apples, cinnamon and sugar in medium bowl; let stand.
Mix together remaining ingredients; beat well.
Layer dough mixture and apples in a greased and floured tube pan.
The last layer is of apples.
Bake 1 3/4 hours at 350°.
Cool in pan until cool.

title: plains cheese ball
directions: Mix together Cheddar cheese, mayonnaise, onion, nuts, black pepper and dash of cayenne. Form with well in middle.
Fill with strawberry or raspberry preserves.

title: ham loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: midnight cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
A good and very easy cake to make.

title: green chile and artichoke dip(serves 15)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain the pimentos.
In a mixing bowl combine the first six ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread mixture into a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese. At this point the dip may be stored in the refrigerator for baking at a later time.
Bake uncovered
in a preheated oven 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Serve hot with tortilla ships.

title: toad in a hole(smaller, quicker version of brunch eggs)
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Break eggs.
Add flour, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Add cheese and sausage.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding according to directions.
In large bowl, layer vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and vanilla pudding. Repeat, then add another layer of bananas.
Top with wafers.

title: date nut bars
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder into bowl.
Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla well.
Add dates and nuts.
Pour over dry ingredients; mix well.
Spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars. Serve plain or dust with powdered sugar.
Makes about 26 (1 x 3-inch) bars.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until just tender.
Drain and cool.
In a bowl, combine remaining ingredients, add carrots and mix lightly. Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
This will keep for 10 days in refrigerator.

title: pepperoni or ham rolls
directions: Prepare rolls recipe (or your favorite bread recipe).
Let rise.
With greased hands flatten each roll on a floured surface. Cover within 1/8-inch of the edge with a thin slice of Velveeta. Then top with thin slices of pepperoni, ham or other.
Roll up and place in greased pan.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 350° for 15 minutes or longer until done (cheese and meat can be more or less to taste).

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt margarine	over low heat, add sugar and stir until dissolved.	Blend
in
flour.
Add	vinegar, stir.	Add sliced beets and heat
through.
Does
not need to cook.
If sauce is too thick or
you
desire
more, add the water from the canned beets and heat through.

title: special chicken casserole
directions: Combine flour, salt and black pepper.
Dip cut up chicken in this seasoned flour mixture.
Brown chicken pieces in butter or oleo.
Transfer to a baking dish.
To butter, add 1 to 2 teaspoons of remaining seasoned flour, minced onion, celery flakes, sweet pepper flakes, nutmeg, dash of m.s.g., mushroom soup, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 5 minutes, then pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in 350° oven until tender, about 1 hour.
Baste.

title: connecticut beef dinner
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet.
Cook and stir meat and onion in shortening until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Add water; heat to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 50 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a square 8 x 8-inch pan.
Arrange prepared apples in pan. Mix together by hand the remaining ingredients and sprinkle over the apples. Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter - your way
directions: Shell peanuts.
Place all ingredients except oil in blender; add oil.

title: mushroom meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Place in a casserole sprayed with Mazola no stick.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: jalapeno-corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions; set aside.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter until vegetables are tender.
Combine rice, sauteed vegetables and the next 4 ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Garnish with green pepper rings, cherry tomatoes and parsley, if desired.
Yields 10 servings.

title: molded salad
directions: Grind orange, carrot and apples and add pineapple and sugar. Let set 1 hour.
Mix Jell-O and boiling water well and add fruit, etc. and set until firm.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Add next six ingredients and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Layer tortillas alternately with mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meal in one
directions: Pat meat into greased casserole. Sprinkle rice over top of meat. Add remaining ingredients in order given. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°. Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: low cholesterol white sauce
directions: Dissolve milk powder in milk.
Place milk and flour into a small covered jar and shake vigorously until mixture is smooth. Pour into a small saucepan and cook over low heat until thickened. Stir constantly.
Add salt, oil and flavoring.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix well and bake in ungreased 11 x 14-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip with chopped apple
directions: Let spinach thaw out, then squeeze out all water and juices. Chop apple in fine pieces and mix with spinach.
Then empty dry vegetable soup mix into bowl.
Mix in sour cream and mayonnaise, and salt, or nature seasoning spices blended.
Mix them real good. Then take a loaf of Hawaiian bread.
Cut out center of the bread. Place spinach dip in center of the bowl made with loaf.
Cut the center of the bread, and place loaf in center of cake plate.
Then place cut bread around loaf.

title: coconut dessert
directions: Mix crackers, sugar and margarine.
Reserve 3/4 cup for top. Press the rest into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip milk and pudding together and add softened ice cream. Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer over crackers.
Sprinkle rest of cracker mixture on top.
Freeze. Take out of freezer a short time before serving.

title: "big boy" strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water in pan over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool in refrigerator about 10 minutes.
Don't let it thicken.
Prepare the strawberries and put them in pie shell.
Pour the mixture over the berries (you'll have some leftover) and let set.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: ritz torte
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add sugar, crackers, baking powder and nuts.
Pour into a 10 x 10-inch or 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
When cold, whip cream, sugar and vanilla. Spread over cold torte.
Top with Hershey's shavings and refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well with a mixer.
Add raisins and chopped walnuts.
Pour into 4 (1 pound) greased coffee cans, half full.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm or roll into foil and refrigerate.

title: cocoa drops
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs; stir in butter, milk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add nuts.
Combine with cream mixture and let stand 1 hour.
Bake at 400° in a greased cookie sheet.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add milk and yolks.
Cook and stir constantly over medium heat until thick.
Add vanilla and coconut. Pour in baked pie shell and cover with meringue.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Brown chicken and place in a roasting pan. In saucepan, combine all other ingredients and simmer until smooth, thick and glossy. Spoon over chicken. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Stir only 2 or 3 times during cooking.

title: honey drops
directions: Mix well together honey, sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop cookies on ungreased cookie sheet, then flatten with a glass dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken filled biscuits
directions: Chop chicken; combine with cream cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
On lightly floured board, roll or punch each biscuit to a 4-inch diameter or larger if preferred.
Moisten edges with water.
Place a tablespoon of chicken mixture in center of dough.
Fold up 3 sides of dough and pinch at middle to seal.
Bake on lightly greased baking sheet until golden (400°) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Serve 10.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Mix 2 cups flour and yeast with a wooden spoon.
In saucepan, cook milk, butter and molasses (can use 1/4 cup sugar instead) until butter melts (not boiling).
Pour over mixture.
Add egg, beat at low speed for 3 minutes.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed. Remove from mixer and gradually stir in 1 1/4 cups flour.
Beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Beat again 5 minutes.
Let raise 30 minutes or twice its size.
Makes 20 rolls.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch oblong pan with shortening or butter.
Open pineapple and spread on bottom of pan. Open pie filling and spread over top of pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over top of pie filling.
Sprinkle pecan pieces over cake mix.
Thinly slice butter or margarine over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes.

title: apple mallow yam-yums
directions: In a large bowl, toss apples,
nuts, sugar and spices.
In a casserole, alternate layers of yams and apples.
Dot with margarine and cover.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows; broil until brown.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an 8-inch pie plate.
In small bowl, beat eggs; blend in sugar and oleo.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt; add to butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts (if desired).
Pour into prepared pie plate.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until almost set.
Pie will not test done in center; cool.
Cut into wedges and serve with scoop of ice cream and drizzle with Hot Fudge Sauce (see recipe for sauce).
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: texas barbecue brisket
directions: Rub brisket with tenderizing salt. Place in pan, fat side up. Stir together liquid smoke, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over meat and cover tightly with foil. Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour, reduce heat to 200° and cook for 7 to 8 hours.
To serve, slice across the grain.
Makes delicious sandwiches.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except catsup.
Shape mixture into a loaf.
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Spread 1/4 cup catsup on top of meat loaf.
Bake in 350° oven about 25 minutes.

title: sugar cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add baking soda to milk.
Alternate milk with dry ingredients, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in flavorings.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: wheaties cookies
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar. Add beaten eggs and mix well. Add coconut. Sift flour once before measuring. Then sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together and add to first mixture. Add vanilla and the Wheaties. Roll into balls the size of walnuts. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or so.

title: scalloped corn souffle
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add whole kernel corn (do not drain), cream style corn, beaten eggs and corn muffin mix. Top with sour cream and cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Do not overbake.
Makes a large casserole.

title: thimble cookies
directions: Combine the flour and pecans in a blender or food processor. Process until pecans are very fine. In medium mixing bowl, beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy. Stir in flour mixture. Wrap dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: sliced fruit bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder, then add softened oleo and mix well with cherries, pineapple, eggs and vanilla.
Work dough until easy to work with.
Then divide dough and roll into ropes. Place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When done, cool slightly and cut about 1-inch apart diagonally.
You could frost them before cutting or use powdered sugar.

title: six-layer dips
directions: For first layer, peel avocados and mash with fork.
Mix avocados, lemon juice, mayonnaise, and garlic powder.
Spread on bottom of serving dish.
Next, layer in order, the sour cream, picante sauce, black olives, tomatoes, and Cheddar cheese.	Serve with large corn chips or tortilla chips.
Enjoy!

title: texas brownies
directions: Pour on a greased 11 x 17-inch sheet for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: white cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Beat cream cheese until smooth and add
all ingredients, continue beating until blended.
Refrigerate until firm, at least 2 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and form into 2 balls or logs.
Roll in pecans and wrap in waxed paper.
Keep chilled until ready to serve. Serve with crackers or chips.
May be frozen.

title: microwave potato salad
directions: Place cubed potato in small microwave dish.
Sprinkle with water and cover.
Cook on High for 3 to 4 minutes; stirring once. Cool; mix remaining ingredients; stir well and refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions, adding half the Creme de Menthe to the batter.
Bake in 13x9-inch pan.
Cool. Cover with fudge topping.
Add remaining Creme de Menthe to Cool Whip and spread over fudge topping.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken-fried steak
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper evenly over steaks.
Set aside. Combine cracker crumbs, 1 cup flour, baking powder, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon black pepper and red pepper.
Whisk together 3/4 cup milk and eggs.
Dredge steaks in cracker crumb mixture; dip in milk mixture and dredge in cracker mixture again.
Pour oil into a 12-inch skillet; heat to 360°.
(Do not use a nonstick skillet.) Fry steaks 10 minutes.
Turn and fry 4 to 5 more minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to a wire rack on a jellyroll pan.
Keep steaks warm in a 225° oven.
Carefully drain hot oil, reserving cooked bits and 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat; remove fat.
Add onion and cook until onion is transparent.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until thick, stirring occasionally.
Serve on hamburger buns with a slice of American cheese and a slice of sweet onion.

title: saucy franks
directions: Cut hot dogs 1/4-inch thick.
Mix jelly and mustard together. Put all ingredients into a pot.
Simmer 25 minutes.
Serve warm. Be sure to try the Fancy Saucy Franks.

title: make ahead breakfast bake
directions: Cut up and brown bacon; add onion and cook until clear.
Add clean cut up green beans.
Stir and steam 5 or 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste and add boiling water.
Cook until tender.
New potatoes can be added.

title: egg foo yung
directions: In medium bowl, combine eggs, salt and pepper; beat until frothy.
Finely chop mushrooms and saute in 1 tablespoon oil in small skillet.
Cook mushrooms for 1 minute.
Stir into egg mixture.
Wash and drain bean sprouts (chop shrimp, if using). Mix sprouts, shrimp, ham or pork, chopped onions and celery into egg mixture.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes.
Add sugar.
Stir in pumpkin, lemon juice, flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, powdered sugar and 1 stick softened butter and pour over crumbs.
Top with pineapple, bananas, Cool Whip, nuts and cherries in that order and refrigerate.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding together.
Add rum.
Put bowl of dip next to fruit.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake(no bake)
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Fold in whipped topping and chocolate chips. Spoon into crust and chill for 4 hours until set.

title: hazel's meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Form into a loaf.
Spread catsup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover with foil for first hour.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Mix cheese, seasonings (except paprika) and mayonnaise.
Cut celery sticks into 3-inch lengths.
Fill with cheese mixture. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chicken fricassee and dumplings
directions: Put Bisquick, salt, paprika, salt and pepper in a plastic bag and shake chicken to coat thoroughly.
Melt shortening and butter in a large skillet; brown chicken on all sides.
Remove chicken, drain fat, stir in soup and milk.
Add chicken.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Twenty minutes before chicken should be done cooking, prepare dumpling mix.
Add parsley flakes and poultry seasoning to dough before adding liquids.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto hot chicken and cook uncovered 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: louella's pecan pie(from the mopac in texas)
directions: Whip the eggs and sugar first, then add all other ingredients. Add the chopped pecans.
Pour into crust and decorate top with half of the pecans.

title: strawberry bavarian cream
directions: Drain fruit in large strainer, reserving liquid.
Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add enough cold water to reserve strawberry liquid to make 2 cups.
Add to Jell-O and stir well.
Chill until almost set, then fold in Cool Whip and strawberries.
Pour into Jel-Ring.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours.

title: chocolate chunk brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Add the sugar, eggs, cocoa, vanilla and flour. Coarsely chop the chocolate squares, keeping in large chunks.
Mix the chocolate and nuts with the batter.

title: linzertorte
directions: Cream the butter and sugar, then add grated peels and yolks and beat well.
Sift together the dry ingredients except the nuts and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in the nuts last and work the dough with hands until smooth.
Chill well.
Butter a spring-form cake pan (8-inch with high sides).
Take 2/3 of dough and press it into the pan, making a 1-inch edge around it.
Spread most of preserves over top (should not reach top of edge).
With remaining dough, form long strips about 1/2 inch across and place them on the cake in a lattice pattern.
Fill the squares with more preserves.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool before cutting.
This torte is delicious as it is.
Also, lovely with whipped cream.
Cut it into small pieces for it is very rich.

title: chile dogs
directions: Boil hot dogs in saucepan over medium heat on top of stove. Heat chile over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Serve chile, grated cheese and chopped onion over hot dogs.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Spray skillet with cooking spray.
Cook chicken until done, about 5 minutes per side.
Remove from skillet.
Mix 1 tablespoon pineapple juice with cornstarch until smooth.
Add pineapple, mustard and sugar to pan.
Bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch.
Heat until thick and clear.
Add chicken back to skillet.
Heat through and serve with rice.
Serves 4.
Three grams fat.

title: rocky roads
directions: Melt chocolate in top of a double boiler over hot, not boiling, water.
Stir mixture until smooth.
Remove from heat; spoon half the mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch foil-lined pan. Spread to edges.
Return remaining chocolate to heat.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Cut the broccoli tops into flowerets.
Cut off the top 3-inches of the stems.
Peel them and cut them into thin strips, about 1 1/2-inches long.
Cook flowerets and stems, covered, in 3 inches boiling salted water until just barely tender, 4 to 5 minutes. Drain.

title: pie crust(double for 2-crust pie)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Blend in shortening with pastry blender. Add and blend in water a little at a time.
Blend well, but do not play with it too much or it will not be as flaky.
Roll out on well-floured surface.
If to be used for a cream pie, pierce bottom and sides of crust with a fork and bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.
For fruit pies, use unbaked.

title: broccoli sunflower seed salad
directions: Break broccoli into bite size pieces.
Toss with bacon, sunflower seeds and onion.
Refrigerate, covered.
Before serving, toss with dressing.
Makes large salad.

title: onion loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In a bowl combine cheese and onion with dry ingredients of hot roll mix. Prepare mix according to pkg. directions. Turn onto a floured surface, knead until smooth and elastic, about 6-8 minutes. Shape into a 5-inch ball and place on a greased baking sheet. Cover and let rise in a warm place for 30 minutes or until doubled in size. Bake for 25-35 minutes or until golden brown. Brush with oil or butter. Remove to wire rack to cool or serve immediately.

title: strawberry jam bars
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar; add egg yolks.
Gradually add flour; stir in nuts.
Divide batter.
Spread half in a 9-inch square pan.
Spread other half on waxed paper and shape into a 9-inch square.
Place in refrigerator to make handling easier. Spread jam on batter in pan.
Place refrigerated batter on top. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: In blender container or food processor bowl, combine undrained fruit cocktail, milk, milk powder, yogurt, vanilla and a few dashes of desired spice.
Cover and blend until combined.
Add ice cubes; cover and blend until smooth.
Sprinkle each serving with additional ground cinnamon or nutmeg, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, eggs and blackberry jam.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with sweet milk and buttermilk.
Add chopped pecans.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat 2/3 c. sugar into egg yolks; add salt, stir in milk and cook over medium heat for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add in 6 Tbsp. sugar, beating to soft peaks.
Add to cooked custard and mix thoroughly.
Add flavoring.
Chill 3-4 hours.

title: banana-walnut bread
directions: Beat butter and sugar with mixer until creamy. Add eggs. Beat well; blend in bananas. Blend flour, baking powder, baking soda and nutmeg together and gradually stir dry ingredients into banana mixture. Fold in nuts. Pour batter into 2 lightly greased loaf pans. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° or until done. Toothpick should come out clean and loaf be golden brown. Wrap after cool for a moist bread.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Mix eggs in a large bowl. Add cooking oil, vanilla, liquid sweetener or Sugar Twin.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Cook in water the raisins until tender. Drain and cool.
Add crushed pineapple. Add juice also, mashed bananas or applesauce (no sugar).
Do not use both. Add the pecans or walnuts (optional). Mix all together and pour into angel food baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Sift and blend flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Cream butter and sugar; stir until fluffy.
Stir in eggs.
Sift about 1/4 cup of flour mixture over mixture in bowl and mix well.
Stir in about 1/3 cup of water; add remainder of flour and water alternately, stirring between each addition until smooth.
Follow Solomon's advice for making good men out of growing boys (Proverbs 23:13), and beat well, by hand at least 8 to 10 minutes.
Add honey, raisins, chopped figs and walnuts.
Stir until well mixed. Pour into 10-inch greased tube pan and bake at 350° for about 90 minutes, until toothpick inserted near center will come out clean.

title: pecan whiskey cake
directions: Blend flour and baking powder.
Mix in nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside, reserving 1/4 cup.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients;
beat
for 18 minutes.
Pour in a greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° about 25 minutes or until an inserted knife comes out clean.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine all
ingredients
and
pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yield: 1 pie.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour and salt.
With pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor fashion, cut in lard until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.

title: tomato ham soup
directions: Make about 1 1/4 hours before serving.
In 8-quart Dutch oven or saucepot over medium-high heat in hot salad oil, cook cabbage and onions until lightly browned, about 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add next 6 ingredients; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve half of soup immediately.
Ladle remaining soup into freezer-safe container, leaving at least 1 inch of space at top of container.
Freeze to serve later.
Recipe makes 15 cups or 8 main dish servings.

title: summertime fruit punch
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients, then gently stir in ginger ale.
Makes 1 gallon.
This punch is tart and refreshing.

title: fried asparagus
directions: Wash and trim bottoms of fresh asparagus.
Cut asparagus in 1/2-inch diagonal slices.
Melt Crisco in large skillet.
Saute asparagus for about 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper. Serve hot.

title: fried cheese balls
directions: Mix together the eggs, milk and water, alternating small amounts of each.
Set aside.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt and then add to egg mixture.
Add cheese and blend well.
Deep fry in skillet on medium-high; drop by teaspoonfuls.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a separate bowl, mix eggs, soups, mayonnaise, cheese and onion.
Mix together and add broccoli.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Can make smaller casserole, approximately 8 x 8-inch by cutting recipe in half and using 1 can of soup.)

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients (except bread crumbs) in a bowl.
Place in ungreased casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Remove, top with bread crumbs and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: artichoke-green bean casserole
directions: Spray medium size casserole with nonstick spray.
Mix ingredients in casserole with enough liquid from artichokes so ingredients will be moist but not too watery.
Sprinkle top with reserved bread crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° until beans are done, about one hour.
Remainingg liquid from artichokes may be reserved in refrigerator for reheating leftovers if beans become too dry.

title: keep forever slaw - i
directions: Shred vegetables to your liking.
Toss vegetables together and put in a bowl with a tight fitting lid.
Pour 7/8 cup of sugar over vegetables and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients to a saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Let dressing mixture cool and pour over vegetables.
Do not stir.
Cover slaw mixture and refrigerate for 24 hours or more.
Stir when ready to serve.
Keeps well for several days.

title: make-ahead potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes in salted water; drain.
Combine all, except butter and cheese, while still hot; whip or mash until fluffy.
Spread in large casserole or divide into 2 casseroles (buttered).
Refrigerate or freeze until ready to use.

title: caramelitas
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together to make crust.
Press half of crust mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: mama's ginger cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Sift flour, baking powder and all spices together.
Measure molasses (sorghum is best) in a larger than 1 cup measure.
Add soda and stir, pouring into cake mixture as it "works".
Add extract to water and to eggs and Crisco and molasses mixture.
(I like to use tepid water and "wash out" molasses cup with it.)
Add flour mixture alternately with water in small amounts.
Pour into a greased and floured large cake pan (about 10 x 7-inch).
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes. Raisins or nuts or both may be added.

title: fig preserves
directions: Sprinkle ripe figs with 1 cup baking soda, cover with 6-quarts of boiling water and let stand 15 minutes.
Drain and wash in 2 baths of clean, cold water and drain.

title: deer meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours (at 325° for glass pan) in a loaf pan.
The last 1/2 hour, put ketchup or more Heinz 57 on top.

title: banana loaf(diabetic)
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together egg whites, bananas, sugar, oil and vanilla.
In a small bowl, stir together flour, walnuts, raisins and baking powder.
Stir into banana mixture until well mixed.
Turn into a greased and floured 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Yields 1 loaf, 16 slices.
Exchange, 1 slice:
2 bread.
Calories:
1 slice 160.

title: fettucine abruzzese
directions: Heat olive oil in pan.
Saute garlic until golden.
Add mushrooms and saute until soft.
Add red pepper, parsley and broth and heat for 5 minutes.
Cook fettucine until "al dente."
Drain and add to pan.
Toss to combine.
Add cheese and toss again.

title: chili with venison burger
directions: Fry meat, onion and garlic in oil until meat turns color.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until thick, stirring occasionally.
This is excellent over rice.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ginger ale; chill thoroughly.
Chill ginger ale and add immediately before serving.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Cook egg yolks, sugar, salt, vinegar, pineapple syrup and margarine in double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream, light cherries, marshmallows, pineapple and oranges.
Chill 24 hours.
Decorate top with orange sections and maraschino cherries.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: aunt lily pipes gumdrop cake
directions: Cut raisins and gumdrops into small pieces, dredge with flour. Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, applesauce, water and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add raisins and gumdrops.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Glaze cooled cake.

title: rice and apricot stuffing(for duck or chicken)
directions: Heat butter.
Add onion, parsley and celery.
Cook about 5 minutes, or until soft but not browned.
Add rice and apricots, tossing together lightly.
Season with savory and salt and pepper to taste.
Makes enough for a 5-pound chicken or duck.

title: rum balls
directions: Blend the wafers, then the pecans in the blender.
Mix and add other ingredients.
Coat hands with confectioners sugar and roll into small balls.
Refrigerate 1 hour then roll in confectioners sugar.

title: mother's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together.
In separate bowl, beat milk and egg yolks together; strain.
Mix all ingredients and cook in double boiler or heavy sauce pan until very thick.
Pour into cooked pie crust.
Dot with butter.
Beat egg whites until fluffy. Add 4 Tbsp. sugar and beat until stiff peaks.
Pour over pie and brown in preheated 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: amish bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Grease loaf pan with Crisco only. Bake at 300° to 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: onion pie
directions: Prebake pastry shell upside down in a 400° oven.
Place an empty pie tin on top of the pie crust to keep it smooth.

title: my mom's raisin pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, steamed raisins and nuts.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into mixture very lightly. Pour filling into unbaked pastry shell and bake slowly for 45 minutes.
It forms its own crust.
Yields 9-inch pie.

title: sue bailey's pecan pralines
directions: Bring 4 cups sugar and 1 cup milk to a boil, then add the browned sugar, Karo, soda and salt.
Boil until it reaches the soft ball stage on candy thermometer.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Continue stirring until mixture is thick and then drop on wax paper.
Makes 50 to 70 pieces.

title: fudge
directions: In a very large saucepan, bring to a boil the sugar and milk. Stirring constantly, boil 6 minutes.
Remove from heat; let set for 2 minutes, then add remaining ingredients.
Beat by hand or electric mixer until creamy.
Line large cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Spread fudge evenly onto cookie sheet.
When completely cooked, flip fudge onto more waxed paper.
Spread out on table or countertop.
Cut.
Enjoy!
Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: refrigerated whipped potatoes
directions: Cook peeled potatoes. Add other ingredients and beat until fluffy; cool. Cover and place in refrigerator. May be used anytime within 2 weeks.
Place desired amount in casserole. Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: grape-nuts pie
directions: Combine cereal and water.
Let stand until water is absorbed. Blend eggs with sugar and corn syrup, butter, vanilla and salt; fold into softened cereal. Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350° or until puffy.
Add whipped cream if desired when served.

title: ham and egg casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, then add layer of cubed ham, next add layer of grated cheese, reserve 1/2 cup of cheese.
Mix eggs, mustard and 2 1/2 cups of milk.
Pour this over first mixture in pan.
Mix mushroom soup and 1/2 cup milk; pour this over egg mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese over top. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for about 90 minutes.
Don't bake too fast.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cabbage with cheese
directions: Cut cabbage in 1-inch squares; cook in water 5 minutes. Drain.
Add to soup, mushrooms plus 1/2 can of mushroom liquid, and cheese.
Heat.
Put cabbage in casserole; pour mixture on top. Top with crumbs.
Bake in 325° oven until bubbly (about 30 minutes or so).

title: chess cake *
directions: Combine cake mix, egg and margarine.
Dough is thick, about the consistency of cookie dough.
Pat dough into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 3 eggs.
Pour over dough in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cake falls in middle and is a bit gooey.

title: lentil soup
directions: Add water to cover lentils.
Cook at medium heat for 45 minutes or until done.
Also goes well with cornbread.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil together 2 sticks butter, 4 tablespoons cocoa and 1 cup water.
Then add flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, soda, sour cream and vanilla.
Bake on large, ungreased cookie sheet.

title: easy frosting
directions: Mix milk, butter and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil, then remove from heat.
Add vanilla and chips.
Stir or beat until frosting is of a spreading consistency.

title: lemon cake pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add juice of lemon, egg yolks, flour and milk.
Stir well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Place dish in pan of hot water.
Bake 45 minutes until top is golden brown.
Extra good with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots (cut in wheels) until tender; drain.
Then mix with pepper and onion, raw.
Heat other ingredients and pour over vegetables while hot.
Refrigerate.
Serve as salad.
Will keep for weeks.

title: pastry dough
directions: Combine flour and salt, then mix in Crisco.
Use dough cutter until small pin size.
Add water slowly while mixing until mixture is moist.
Roll pastry dough to size of pan.
Put on top of pre-filling.
Have oven hot on 350°.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours or until brown.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix flour, cayenne pepper and mustard.
Cut in shortening and fold in cheese.
Drop or roll and place on cookie sheet.
May brush with melted butter and sprinkle on garlic powder. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: 8 day pickles
directions: Dissolve salt in water and pour over cucumbers.
Let these stand 7 days, stirring occasionally.
Remove brine and pour scalding water over pickles and let remain 1 day.
Drain and cover with scalding water again in which a chunk of alum the size of a walnut has been dissolved.
Drain again and cover with vinegar (not too strong) in which sugar, cinnamon bark, horseradish and allspice have been added.
Repeat each day for 3 days.
These may be kept in open jar or canned.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond bark and pour over other ingredients.
Mix well. Spread out on wax paper.

title: french pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks. Add rest in above order.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Between frying, mix gently with wire whip.

title: lemon lime refrigerator cake
directions: Bake cake as instructed on box.
Cool cake.
Punch holes in cake.
Dissolve lime jello in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add
1/2 cup cold water, pour Jell-O over cake and refrigerate.

title: deluxe fudge brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan over low heat; cool slightly.
Beat eggs slightly, then gradually beat in sugar and continue beating for 2 to 3 minutes.
Blend in chocolate mixture. Stir in flour, then add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: cinnamon crisps(really easy and very good...)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift together dry ingredients. Combine the two mixtures.
Pat onto greased cookie sheets (takes two), spreading very thin.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in pie crusts at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy cake recipe
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box and bake in 9x13 inch pan. Let cake cool and the poke holes all over cake. Pour on crushed pineapples with juice. Make pudding as directed and spread on top of cake. Top with Cool Whip.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Open crescent rolls out and place on pizza pan; spread to cover the pan and bake.
Mix mayonnaise, milk and cream cheese. Spread this over the cooled crescent roll pastry.
Cut vegetables very small and place on top of the cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with a little garlic salt if desired.

title: sweet and spicy cucumbers
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar, garlic powder and crushed red pepper until sugar melts.
Slice cucumbers and onions.
Pour sugar mixture over sliced cucumbers and onions.
Chill before serving.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons of lukewarm water.
Stir dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add 2 cups of warm buttermilk and yeast mixture to dry ingredients.
Put in bowl and cover with Reynolds Wrap.
Store in refrigerator for 12 hours. Roll and cut out like biscuits and let stand at room temperature 25 to 30 minutes.
Brush with butter and bake at 400° about 15 minutes.

title: lye soap
directions: There are bound to be some readers who can remember when wash day meant heating water in a black iron pot and using strong lye soap and a rub board to get clothes clean.

title: super salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together flour, baking soda, salt, 1 teaspoon vanilla, eggs, 2 cups sugar and pineapple.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle on brown sugar, coconut and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Mix butter, milk, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; pour over cake as soon as it comes from oven.

title: party sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage and cheese.
Add Bismix.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes. Serve hot or cold.

title: wild rice stuffing
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, but do not let it dry out completely.
Should be moist.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Turn stove off.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Add cornflakes.
Stir them in.
Spoon out on foil or wax paper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Saute onions in butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in buttered casserole dish uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
To make a main dish out of this, add chicken with a small amount of broth.

title: quick pizza dough
directions: Mix together yeast and water; let stand 5 minutes.
Add and mix
the salt, sugar, oil and flour (1 1/2 cups at a time).
Shape and let stand in pan for 15 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven with your favorite pizza sauce or toppings.
Makes one pizza.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon until lightly browned.
Add onions and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Chop clams.
Add enough water to clam liquid to make 2 cups.
Stir flour into onion mixture until blended.
Gradually stir in clam mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is slightly thickened.
Stir in potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes.
Add clams, milk, butter or margarine and cover and cook until heated through for about 5 minutes, stirring often.
Makes 10 cups or 5 servings.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Place blueberry pie filling in 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole. Dot with butter or sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: pumpkin nut muffins
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin in a large mixing bowl. Mix well.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking soda and spices. Add flour mixture and pecans to pumpkin mixture.
Combine just until blended.
Do not overmix.
Fill muffin liners 3/4 full. Combine an additional 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle on top of muffins.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 48 muffins.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all well. Add Fritos corn chips to taste.

title: country style smothered chicken
directions: Cut up chicken; salt.
Roll each piece in flour and place in roaster.
Lay 4 or 5 slices of bacon, 1/2 onion (sliced) and celery leaves on top.
Cover with water and bake for 3 hours.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy taco dinner
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is light brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix and water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.
Spoon beef mixture onto chips and top with remaining ingredients.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix together; let stand 15 minutes.
Roll thin and round into a number of pieces.
Drop in hot oil for approximately 3 minutes. Serve hot.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Add chicken, peas, diced celery, diced onion, pimientos and chopped sweet pickles.
Mix well.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Blend soups, broth, chilies and salsa.
Layer chips, chicken, soup mixture and cheese in a casserole dish.
Repeat layers until all are used, topping with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or in crock-pot on low for several hours.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels and milk in double boiler.
Add pecans and mix well.
Drop and shape on wax paper and let harden.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip candies in chocolate with toothpick and piece on wax paper to harden.

title: vermont maple cookies
directions: Add butter or margarine and maple syrup to the egg.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot cocoa
directions: In
medium
saucepan,
combine	sugar,	cocoa and salt; blend in	water.	Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture
boils.
Boil
and	stir
2 minutes.
Add milk. Stir
and heat
to serving temperature.
Do not boil.
