Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Beat with rotary beater or wire whisk until foamy.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Mix margarine and Crisco.
Blend in sugar.
Gradually add flour and eggs; mix well.
Add flavoring and blend well.
When mixture is smooth, add Seven-Up.
Mix until blended.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: diabetic pound cake
directions: Sift flour and soda; add oil and sugar substitute.
Mix well until light.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Beat well. Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 or more minutes.

title: elbert's goulash
directions: Put all ingredients into skillet and cook until potatoes are done.
Add cornmeal and cook until brown.

title: blue or roquefort cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill preferably overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Use within a week.
Yield: about 1 1/2 cups.

title: colby fiesta salad
directions: Warm tortillas and place in a 4 or 5-inch container to bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cook meat, then add taco seasoning and water.
Heat.
Set aside.
Bring milk to a boil and add cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Add jalapeno peppers, if desired. Keep warm.
Place tortilla bowls on plate.
Divide lettuce, tomato and onion equally.
Top with equal portions of meat, then cheese sauce.
Place 2 olives in each bowl.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix and press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Be sure to press some of the crust up the sides of the pan.

title: savory meatballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first 8 ingredients.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape into 2-inch balls.
In a skillet, melt the shortening over medium-high heat.
Brown meatballs.
Place in a casserole dish.
Combine soup and water; pour over meatballs. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach leaves and snap off stems.
Spin dry in a salad spinner or drain on paper towels.
Slice red onion or green onions; put aside.
Slice hard-boiled eggs in the egg slicer twice, turning them the second time.
Tear spinach leaves in small pieces; add onions.
Pour on salad dressing (recipe below) and toss.
Top with egg and bacon.

title: cranberry pistachio biscotti
directions: In a bowl combine cranberries with enough hot water to cover and soak 5 minutes.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Blend flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating until a dough forms (takes a while!).
Stir in cranberries and pistachios.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead several times and divide dough.
Working on large greased and floured baking sheet, with floured hands, form each piece of dough into log, 13 inches long and 2 inches wide, flatten top.
Arrange logs three inches apart on sheet and brush with egg wash.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes at 325° and let cool on the baking sheet on a rack for 10 minutes.

title: spice 'n sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Mix at low speed until well blended.
Drop by teaspoons into colored sugar or decorettes; roll to coat.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; if desired, flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute, then remove from cookie sheet.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix the Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs together.
Salt the chicken breasts and roll in mixture.
Fry in oil until brown on both sides.

title: german cole slaw
directions: In large bowl, mix cabbage, onion and carrot. Set aside. Boil for 3 minutes the sugar and vinegar. Cool mixture by placing pan in sink in cold water. Add oil and celery seed. Pour marinade over vegetables and allow to sit out for about 6 hours, stirring occasionally. If made in the morning, store in refrigerator by evening.

title: yayeg (armenian cucumber salad)
directions: Peel, dice and salt cucumbers.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, beat yogurt with a little water.
Combine cucumbers and yogurt. Chop the mint leaves and sprinkle on top.
Serve chilled.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Cover 8
x 8-inch baking dish with brown sugar 1/2 inch thick. Beat
yolks
together
with sugar until smooth.
Place pineapple over
sugar (brown).
Put 1 cherry in center of each pineapple.

title: easy custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer on high for 3 minutes or until well blended.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 40 minutes, or until knife inserted comes out clean. It will form its own crust.

title: april's chocolate covered strawberries
directions: Melt chocolate in the top of a double boiler.
With a wooden spoon, stir in cream, rum and butter.
Remove from heat.
Holding strawberry by the stem, dip into chocolate, covering the tip and one side of the berry.
Place strawberries, chocolate side down, on a baking sheet lined with waxed paper and chill.

title: pinwheels
directions: Combine cream cheese, taco seasoning mix, sour cream and picante sauce and mix well.
Spread 2 tablespoons, approximately, cream cheese mixture evenly over each tortilla.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese, black olives and onions.
Roll tortilla up tightly. Cover rolls with plastic wrap, refrigerate 2 hours.
Slice each roll into 1/2 inch slices.
Serve with picante sauce for dipping.

title: no bake peanut butter chews
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and butter.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over cornflakes and stir until the flakes are well coated.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Stand until slightly cool, then press together (not too firm or they will lose their gloss).

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and condensed milk.
Add other ingredients and pour into pie crusts.
Chill.

title: mrs. morrows meat loaf
directions: Put salt, pepper and seasoned salt on hamburger meat.
Mix the rest, all in well.
Cook about one hour.
Drain.
Add ketchup on top and cook a little longer.
Cook at 350°.

title: nutmeg rolls
directions: Sift together flour and nutmeg.
Set aside.
Cream butter. Gradually add sugar to the butter and cream well.
Blend in egg, vanilla and rum flavoring.
Add gradually to the dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: american chop suey
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Fry hamburg lightly. Salt and pepper.
Add
vegetable
soup and both cans of tomato soup, plus two cans of water.
Heat through and serve.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients but ginger ale.
Put in gallon container and freeze (ice cream but is good).
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Serves about 25.

title: munoz mexican salsa
directions: Add all ingredients except 1 quart of vinegar in heavy cooker, stirring constantly.
Slowly add remaining vinegar as needed to keep mixture from sticking and thin enough to cook.
Will thicken when cool.
Cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter, powdered sugar and margarine.
Spread in a baking pan.
Melt chocolate bits and spread over top of peanut butter mixture.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream together sugar and softened butter or margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in chocolate syrup and flour until blended.
(Batter will look curdled.)
Stir in nuts.
Pour mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool slightly; top with Chocolate Glaze.
Cut into bars.

title: honey mustard baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Arrange chicken in a large shallow pan. Melt butter or oleo in saucepan. Stir in honey, mustard, curry powder and salt. Cook until heated through.
Brush over chicken. Bake 1 1/4 hours or until golden brown.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Mix together Ragu and hamburger.
Boil shells halfway.
Mix cheese, egg, salt and pepper.
Stuff mixture in shells.
put half the meat sauce in baking dish.
Lay stuffed shells on sauce and top with remaining sauce.
Bake until bubbly hot at 350 degrees.

title: burger dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator in a sealed container.

title: maple pecan cake
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in white sugar until stiff and glossy.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt into another mixing bowl.
Add brown sugar, oil and half
of milk. Beat 1 minute on medium speed.
Add remaining milk, egg yolks and flavoring.
Beat 1 minute more.
Fold in egg whites and pecans. Bake in greased and floured pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for two 8-inch layers or 30 to 35 minutes for oblong 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan.

title: fluffy cheesecake
directions: Pat 1/2 of mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan; remaining will be sprinkled on top.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend and fold together until all completely mixed.
Will be slightly sticky.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Blend and let come to a boil the sugar, juice from fruit cocktail and pineapple, jello and water.
Cool.

title: easy potato pancakes
directions: Grind potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients and fry in skillet with a bit of oil.
Brown on both sides.
Serve plain or with applesauce or whatever.

title: steak and rice casserole
directions: Cut steak into small strips and brown in skillet in small amount of vegetable oil.
Drain.
Put uncooked rice in a 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Pour soup on top of rice. Add butter and place steak on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: hearty beef and cheese crescent pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large frypan, brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, beans, cumin seed, garlic salt and salt; simmer while preparing crust.

title: barbara bush's apple crisp with orange juice
directions: Mound apples in buttered pie plate (tin) and pour orange juice over them.
In separate bowl, combine the sugar, flour, spices and salt.
Cut in butter until the mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes until apples are tender and topping is crisp.
Serve warm with cream.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind or finely chop tomatoes and peppers.
(I use my food processor.)
Mix with cabbage and onions.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand 4 to 5 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Add the six remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bring to a boiling point.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.
Cold pack for 5 minutes. Opened jars keep for many weeks in the refrigerator.

title: tarsha spann's meat loaf
directions: Mix
all
ingredients in a bowl.
Flatten the meat loaf out in a small pan and take more ketchup and spread evenly on top.
Bake at
375° for 30 minutes.
(The more hamburger, the more ingredients
and
the bigger the pan, the longer it takes to cook.)

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: low-fat lemon cheese bars
directions: Combine dry cake mix, Butter Buds liquid and 1/4 cup Egg Beaters.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture.
Pat remaining mixture into 9 x 13-inch casserole that has been coated with Pam no-stick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: stir-fry chicken spaghetti
directions: Coat a large skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add diced onion, celery, green pepper and garlic; saute until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, paprika, chili powder, cumin and red pepper.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add chicken; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over hot vermicelli.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut ends off zucchini.
Slice in half lengthwise.
Cook in boiling water until softened.
Scoop out the centers, leaving 1/2-inch walls.
Mix zucchini centers with remaining ingredients. Mound into zucchini boats.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix in bowl in order given.
Pour into greased muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 16 muffins.

title: pineapple surprise
directions: Beat eggs with a fork, add rest of ingredients and stir. Spread on a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
While hot, ice with:

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Mix together rice, water and soups.
Pour mixture into 9 X 13 pan that has been prayed with nonstick spray. Lay pork on top and cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour - 1 hour 15 minutes at 350°.
You can substitute chicken breasts for pork chops.

title: chocolate layer delight
directions: Melt margarine.
Place flour and pecans in a mixing bowl. Pour melted margarine over flour mixture and blend well with a fork.
Spread mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chocolate bit cookies
directions: Make dough stiff enough to roll on small balls.
Do not press flat; will flatten while baking.
Usually is right amount of flour.
Do not overbake.

title: honey-pecan rolls
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in just enough milk so dough leaves side of bowl and rounds up into a ball.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly 10 times. Roll into a rectangle.
Mix remaining ingredients; reserve a 1/4 cup.
Spread remaining pecan mixture over rectangle.
Roll up. Pinch edges to seal.
Cut into 6 inches.
Spread remaining pecan mixture over biscuit tops.
Bake for 15 to 17 minutes or until lightly golden brown.

title: trade winds salad
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar in medium saucepan.
Add chicken, turkey or ham and cook until browned.
Cool.
Combine cooked shells, meat mixture, grapes or apples and cheese in a large bowl. Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons of juice.
Add mayonnaise, sour cream, pineapple and juice and salt.
Blend well. Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix oats, flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly. Place half of this mixture in an 8 x 8-inch greased baking dish. Cover with cranberry sauce.
Top with balance of mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot in squares, topped with ice cream.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening together; add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Blend and add flour, soda, coconut and peanuts.
Mix well again.
Form into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: reeses peanut butter candy
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, and sugar together.
Cool.
Roll into small balls.
Using a toothpick, dip peanut butter balls in chocolate and wax that have been melted in double boiler.
Place balls on wax paper to cool.
These freeze well.

title: dutch apple cake with caramel glaze
directions: Position rack in lower third of oven; preheat to 350°.
Grease a 12 cup Bundt pan or a 10 x 4-inch tube pan; dust with flour.

title: wacky cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together and pour into ungreased pan. Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: bean soup mix
directions: Rinse and soak pinto beans, kidney beans, black-eyed beans, split peas, lentils, pearl barley and uncooked rice overnight. Take 2 cups of bean soup mix.
Cook beans in 3 to 4 quarts of water with soup bone, onion, clove of garlic, can green chilies and tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook until beans are done, 2 to 4 hours.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and serve with hot buttered cornbread.

title: fruit with white wine
directions: Note:
Also, you can use mandarin oranges or grapefruit sections.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Put butter and milk in a heavy saucepan over low heat. Combine cocoa, flour and sugar.
Add to milk mixture.
Stir constantly until it thickens.
Add vanilla.

title: mexican deviled eggs
directions: Slice the eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks and set whites aside. In a small bowl, mash yolks with cheese, mayonnaise, salsa, onions, sour cream and salt. Evenly fill the egg whites. Serve immediately or chill until ready to serve.

title: sausage cornbread bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Brown sausage and onion; drain well.
Combine eggs, cornmeal, corn, milk and oil; mix well.
Pour half of mixture into prepared baking dish, then sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Pour other half of cornmeal mixture over top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: southern strawberry shortcake
directions: Roll pie crust out thin and cut in 1 x 3-inch strips.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Remove and immediately take stick of butter and swipe on hot crust.
Cap and wash berries and slice thin slices.
Add sugar to taste.
At serving time place 3 to 4 pieces of crust in bowls and pour berries on top, adding whipped cream.
Delicious!

title: peter's special birthday cake
directions: Bake angel food cake according to directions.
Cool.
Cut into three layers.

title: police boy's chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat sugars and margarine.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
In separate bowl, mix flour, salt, soda and spices.
Slowly add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet (I use thick aluminum sheet).
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.
Remain on cookie sheet for 1 minute.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: peach cobbler supreme
directions: Melt butter in a 7 x 11-inch shallow baking dish.
Sift together dry ingredients; add milk and stir well.
Pour this mixture into the baking dish; do not stir.
Top with peaches, including juice; sprinkle allspice and lemon peel over peaches, but do not stir.
Bake in 350° oven 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown the sausage.
Drain grease off.
Lay bread on the bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Lay the cheese on top and then spread the sausage on that.
Sprinkle green onions on top.
Make two layers, if necessary.
Mix together the beaten eggs, milk, half and half, salt, pepper, Worcestershire, nutmeg, thyme and rosemary.
Pour into casserole.
Cover and store in refrigerator for 10 to 12 hours.
Bake in 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and dice tomato.
Cut avocado in half and remove from skin with a spoon.
Mash avocado with lemon juice.
Stir in other ingredients.
Very tasty!

title: savory green beans 'n bacon
directions: In a medium saucepan, saute onions and bacon until onions are tender; drain.
Stir in the green beans and seasonings.
Cover and heat thoroughly.
Serve over Success| rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.

title: caribbean potato salad
directions: Boil unpeeled whole potatoes.
Boil eggs.
Drain and cool. Peel potatoes and eggs.
Cut into cubes.
Combine potatoes, eggs and drained vegetables.
Mix with equal parts mayonnaise and Durkee's famous sauce.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 reserved liquid.
Mix all. Chill before serving.

title: chicken pie
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Put in chicken.
Top with vegetables.
Mix broth and cream of chicken soup.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Mix flour, margarine and milk; pour on top of casserole and bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Put all other ingredients, except fruit, in the butter; but do not mix.
Pour in fruit.
Sprinkle with sugar (about 3/4 cup).
Bake 5 minutes at 450°, then reduce to 350° and bake 45 more minutes.

title: pineapple chiffon salad
directions: Mix the lemon jello and 1 cup hot pineapple juice, then chill until syrupy.
Add the celery, nuts, mayonnaise and Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Put in a Pyrex dish and let set until firm. Cut in squares.

title: dip for apples
directions: Mix all together.
Judge the amounts for the spices and vanilla by taste, beginning with 1/2 teaspoon.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll in pecans.

title: baked onions
directions: Quarter onions and cover with butter and garlic salt.
Wrap each individual onion in aluminum foil and cook on barbecue grill for around 45 minutes or until onions are tender.
You may also bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: mystery punch
directions: Blend lemonade, orange juice, apple juice and ginger ale.
Add sherbet and stir just a few times.
Add strawberries (do not defrost).
Enjoy.

title: acorn stuffed squash
directions: Halve squash lengthwise and remove strings and seeds.
Bake, covered with foil, until tender, about 25 minutes in a 375° oven. Scoop out flesh, leaving about 1/4-inch shell.
Mash squash well. Saute onion in butter until soft and mix with squash, walnuts, rice, eggs and seasonings.
Heap squash mixture into shells and bake 10 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Top with cheese in the last few minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well. Form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix flour, margarine and sugar
in
mixer or with fork. Then add ground nuts.
Pour in
9 x 13-inch
pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°; cool.

title: snowball cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, dissolve jello in the boiling water. Stir in fruit and 2 packages of Dream Whip (mixed according to package directions).
Pinch chunks of cake into mixture.
Mix well and pat down with spoon.
Mix remaining 2 packages of Dream Whip and spread on top.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix liquids, then add butter, sugar and pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: whiz macaroni
directions: Simmer franks in water 5 minutes.
Drain and slice diagonally. Combine with remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream(for 1 gallon freezer)
directions: Blend in blender.
Pour in ice cream maker.
Fill rest of freezer can with milk (about 1 1/2 inches from the top of can). Stir well.
Place lid on.
Pack with alternating layers of ice and salt.

title: special chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soup and sour cream in bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in crushed crackers.
Spoon into baking dish.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add egg and salt, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in sour milk and vanilla.
Sift flour with soda. Add to creamed mixture.
Add rhubarb.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast sticky buns
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle pecans in pan. Place still frozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 box of pudding mix.
Pour melted margarine over rolls.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over all.
Cover with wax paper and set in cold oven overnight.
In morning, bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Dump immediately.

title: corn bake
directions: Melt butter and beat eggs.
Drain whole corn.
Combine all ingredients; stir.
Add corn muffin mix last.
Pour into 7 x 11-inch dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: uncooked strawberry frozen jam
directions: Slowly sift pectin into crushed berries.
Set aside 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add corn syrup, stirring well. Gradually stir in sugar.
When sugar is dissolved, add lemon juice.

title: easy fruit dessert
directions: Pour fruit and juice in baking pan (8 x 12-inch) or similar size.
Preheat oven to 325°.
If using peaches or pears, chop into small pieces.
Add 1/2 to 1 c. water and sugar to fruit.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Put fruit into oven; heat to boiling in the baking pan.
Mix together flour, 1 cup sugar, milk, baking powder and salt.
Batter will be thin.
Pour over boiling fruit.
Do not stir. Bake at 325° until crust is brown and cooked through.
Batter will rise to the top and form a crust on top.
Watch to see that it doesn't boil and adjust oven accordingly.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done in 350° oven.
Cut in half.
Scoop out both halves.
Reserve the skin.
Whip the potatoes in bowl with salt and pepper to taste.
When smooth, add sour cream, chives, cheese and butter.
Whip until blended.
Spoon mixture back into skins.
Sprinkle with a little Parmesan cheese.
May be held in refrigerator for 24 hours or wrapped for freezing.
To serve, bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until golden.

title: okra, corn and tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients. Simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes in a large skillet over low flame.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar together.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Mash very ripe bananas and add to creamed butter, eggs and sugar mixture, then add flour mix, pecans and vanilla. Bake in tube pan, greased with butter.
Bake at 325° to 350° until brown, about 1 hour.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Cut Twinkies in half lengthwise and layer cream side up in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: borscht
directions: Saute onions and celery in oil until tender.
Add beets, cabbage, water and seasonings.
Simmer until vegies are tender, about 20 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and corn syrup.
Simmer 5 more minutes.
Salt to taste.
Add sour cream just before serving. Sprinkle with dill.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger foil dinner
directions: Place peeled potatoes and carrots in kettle of cold water to hold.
Cut 8 pieces of aluminum foil 12 x 30 inches and fold each piece in half to measure 12 x 15 inches.
Divide beef into 8 equal parts and pat each one flat on each piece of foil.
Place one potato (sliced) on top of each hamburger patty.
Repeat with carrots and onions.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Seal each aluminum foil by rolling edges over each other.
Put on hot coals and turn every 5 minutes.
Cooking time is 15 to 20 minutes.
The contents of these packages are hot.
Be careful.

title: stir-in-snacks
directions: Stir ingredients together. Makes 2 (1 cup) servings.

title: broccoli bread(more like a casserole)
directions: *I prefer to use the broccoli cuts.

title: mom's donuts
directions: Mix all ingredients and add enough flour to make soft dough.

title: apple brandy cake
directions: Combine mixture, then add vanilla, brandy, apples and nuts. Spread into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for abut 40 minutes.
This cake needs no icing and you don't have to use a mixer.

title: seven can soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Then mix all
ingredients and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
No seasonings needed.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups hot water.
Add pineapple and blueberries, juice and all.
Pour in a long dish and let congeal.

title: ziti bake
directions: In 8-quart Dutch oven, prepare ziti according to directions. Drain; set aside.
In same Dutch oven, over medium heat, cook ground beef until well browned, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove Dutch oven from heat.
Stir in Ricotta and next 5 ingredients and half of sauce until well mixed.
Add ziti and toss gently to coat well.
Spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Pour remaining sauce over ziti and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serve with extra sauce if desired.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice in one dish and dry ingredients and mayonnaise in another.
Dip fillets into milk mixture, then press into crumb mixture, coating both sides.
Place in shallow pan and bake 10 to 12 minutes in 450° oven.

title: mexicali chicken n cheese bake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch dish.
In large bowl, combine chicken, 1 cup cheese, corn and soup; blend well.
Pour into baking dish.
Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder and seasoned salt.
Add milk, butter and eggs.
Stir until dry ingredients are moist.
(Batter may appear slightly lumpy.)
Stir in onion, chiles and pimiento.
Pour batter over chicken mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese; return to oven until cheese has melted.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts with bay leaf and celery until tender. Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix sour cream, soups and salad dressing together.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, egg, bread crumbs and salt; shape into 50 small 1/2-inch balls.
Arrange in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch shallow baking pan.
Broil 4 inches from heat until browned; turn once.
Pour off fat.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados. In a medium size bowl, combine avocado, lemon juice, salt and pepper. In another bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix. Spread bean dip on a large shallow serving platter, top with seasoned avocado mixture, layer with sour cream mixture. Sprinkle with chopped onions, tomatoes and olives. Cover with cheddar cheese. Serve chilled or at room temperature.

title: ham and potato casserole(microwave use)
directions: Layer ham, potatoes, onion, cheese and mushroom soup.
Repeat. Add 1/2 cream and 1/2 water.
Microwave 6 minutes; stir.
Microwave 6 minutes; stir.
Microwave 6 minutes; stir.
Microwave 6 minutes; stir.
Microwave 5 minutes; let stand a few minutes before removing from microwave.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding enough clam juice to make right consistency for dipping.
Yields about 1 cup dip.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, Fluff and creme de menthe well.
Add mixture to pie shell and freeze.

title: extra special cookies
directions: Cream sugar, brown sugar, margarine, oil and egg.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda; add with butterscotch chips, coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ed's wild rice casserole
directions: Cook wild rice according to directions; set aside.
Brown sausage; drain, crumble and set aside.
Saute green pepper, celery and scallions.
Mix rice, sausage and vegetables.
Add dry soup mix and chestnuts.
Add water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Cook potatoes approximately 20 minutes, drain and cool slightly.
Mash potatoes and add 1/4 cup butter, salt, sugar, spices and egg yolks.
Refrigerate to chill thoroughly.
Flatten 1/3 cup of mixture into a 3-inch circle.
Place a marshmallow in center.
Gather potato around marshmallow to enclose, leaving a small hole on top.
Set aside and repeat until you have 12 puffs. In a separate bowl, combine crumbs and 1/4 cup melted butter. Roll puffs in buttered crumbs, coating well.
Place puffs on a cookie sheet and freeze until solid.
Remove from freezer and bake frozen puffs for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's pie crust cookies
directions: Heat oven to 425°. With pastry cutter, hands or fork, mix flour, salt and Crisco until crumbly, pea-size clumps. Add water, stirring with fork until ball forms and pulls away from sides of bowl. Flour surface and rolling pin. Roll out dough to 1/8-inch thickness. Spread with soft butter. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Starting at one side, roll crust into a log (jelly roll style) with filling inside. Using table knife, cut into 1-inch pieces. Place cut side down in ungreased 9-inch glass pie plate. Sides of cookies can touch. Bake for 15 minutes or until slightly brown on top. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese on tortillas.
Sprinkle on any or all of the ingredients listed.
Roll and chill 2 hours.
Slice 1/2-inch slices.
Put toothpick through to hold in place.

title: cheesy butterhorns
directions: Blend oleo, cheese and salt. Blend in flour. Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll out as for pie crust and cut into pie shape wedges. Roll up wide to narrow edge.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Frost.
Can sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over dough before rolling up.

title: peanut butter round-up cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugars together until creamy; add eggs and peanut butter.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in Quaker oats. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; with the back of a fork, press to make crisscrosses on each (if dough sticks to fork, occasionally dip fork in flour).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: vanilla frosting
directions: Mix together and cream with mixer.
(Double to frost most cakes.)
Add a little more water if you need to.

title: delicious baked beans
directions: Seed and chop green pepper; chop onion.
Peel and chop tomato. Mix pepper, mustard and paprika with corn syrup, Worcestershire sauce and bacon fat or margarine.
Combine all ingredients with beans and spoon into a buttered 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: fried okra
directions: Rinse okra.
Remove caps, cut pods into 1/2-inch slices.
Toss with cornmeal.
Heat shortening in heavy skillet or electric skillet.
Fry single layer of okra about 8 or 10 minutes until golden brown on all sides.
Do not overcook, or okra will be too soft.
Turn carefully.
Remove and drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo and granulated sugar, add oil and powdered sugar. Add eggs, dry ingredients and vanilla.
Chill well.
Make small balls of dough and roll ball in sugar.
Press down on cookie sheet with glass tumbler dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan well.
Spread coconut and pecans over bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Spread on top of previous mixture.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Add oleo and spoon on top of cake.
Bake at 350° until cake pulls away from cake pan, approximately 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and turn onto serving tray.
Cool and serve.

title: icebox pie
directions: Mix butter with flour and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, and Cool Whip and spread on cooled crust. Beat pistachio pudding and water until firm.
Spread on top of Cool Whip mixture.
Chill until served.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Combine soup mix and rice in a 1 3/4-quart shallow casserole dish; add boiling water, stirring until soup mix is dissolved. Set aside. Combine sausage, celery, green pepper and onion in large skillet; cook until sausage is browned, stirring to crumble. Drain well. Add meat mixture, pimento and water chestnuts to soup mixture; stir well. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: noodles
directions: Roll very, very thin and let dry. Cut in strips and add to favorite broth.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Set aside.
Place half of crumbled cornbread in the bottom of a large serving bowl (I use a 20-cup trifle bowl).
Top with half of beans.

title: banana slush
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add fruit and juices and mashed bananas.
Pour in ice trays and freeze into cubes.
(May be frozen in other containers.)
When ready to serve, pour cold beverage over frozen cubes a few minutes before serving.
Use 3 or 4 cubes to the glass.
